title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Add layers of the following in a bowl:

cake, crushed pineapple, cake, cherry pie filling, cake, vanilla instant pudding (prepared according to package directions), cake, fruit cocktail and top with Cool Whip. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Great for small parties and family get-togethers.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grate cheeses and onion (do not use pre-grated cheese as it's too dry). Use paper towel to oil ring completely. Sprinkle in pecan pieces. Mix cheese, onion and mayo together well. Add pepper and mix. Put into ring and chill 24 hours.

title: beef and black bean soup
directions: Cook beef in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until beef is no longer pink, about 8 minutes.
Stir frequently while cooking to break up into 3/4-inch crumbles.
Pour off drippings. Stir in soup beans, water and salsa.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in green onions.
Garnish with sour cream and cilantro. Makes 4 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: frozen ice pops
directions: Mix all ingredients. Freeze in Dixie cups with popsicle sticks or in popsicle molds.

title: five-can casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Cover generously with crushed potato chips and let stand for at least 30 minutes.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°. Serves six.

title: creamy ham and potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spray 8-inch square glass baking dish (2-quart) with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Spoon into sprayed baking dish. Bake 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese and canned frosting together. pipe in strawberries. Replace tops of strawberries and arrange nicely on serving tray.

title: brochettes of pork with sage
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Cover and marinate at least 15 minutes (the longer the better).
Heat grill. Put pork on skewers or a grill pan.
Cook 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, peanut butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Divide into 3 equal parts. Shape each into roll about 7 inches long.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 4 hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let stand overnight, then sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over very low heat, stirring constantly, or over hot, but not boiling, water.
Measure sugar frosted flakes, then crush to 1 1/2 cups. Set aside.

Sift flour, soda and salt together. Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add dry sifted ingredients; mix thoroughly. Fold in sugar frosted flakes. Swirl warm melted chocolate lightly through batter.
Drop tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: never fail yeast biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
When yeast dissolves, add oil, buttermilk and soda.
Mix real well.
Mix all ingredients well. Dip with spoon onto a greased cookie sheet for biscuits or use muffin pan for rolls.
(Grease pans well.)
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with butter when brown.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Combine prepared vegetables (select 1 cup each of a selection of cauliflowerets, sliced carrots, cherry tomatoes, zucchini, sliced mushrooms, green pepper strips or green beans)
in a 1 quart jar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lila's soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add egg, salt, spices, molasses and sour milk/buttermilk to which soda has been added. Add enough flour to make a dough of rolling consistency. Roll out on floured surface to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutter and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 6 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cinnamon cut-outs
directions: Mix together to form a ball.
Sprinkle cutting board with cinnamon.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out dough with heart-shaped cutter.
Using a toothpick, poke hole in center top of cut-out.
Place on cake rack and air dry completely or dry on rack placed on cookie sheet in a 150° oven for 6 hours, leaving oven door ajar.
(Use knifeblade in door.)

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, eggs and cheeses.
Add macaroni; stir thoroughly.
Put in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° in the oven for 45 minutes, until browned on top.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine spinach, zucchini, cottage cheese, mushrooms, carrots, onions, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel. Saute onion in drippings until tender. Place spinach and small amount of water in saucepan; cover and cook until tender, approximately 8 minutes. Drain well and place in large bowl. Add onion, 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs, milk, eggs, margarine, salt and pepper; mix together. Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with bacon and the remaining crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: persimmon date nut bar
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir soda into persimmon pulp, add to creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, clove and salt; then add to mixture.
Blend in lemon rind, dates and nuts.
Turn into well-greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, 4 eggs and applesauce, then the remaining items and mix all together well.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: white house hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in large baking pan.

title: monterey chicken fajitas
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken until browned, stirring often.
Add pepper and onion and cook over medium heat until tender-crisp.
Add soup and salsa and heat through.
Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla.
Top with cheese and more salsa.
Fold tortilla around filling.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix cocoa, vanilla and food coloring in a small bowl or cup.
Add to oil mixture.
Mix in flour and buttermilk.
Add salt and soda; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in greased and floured cake pans.

title: grape salad
directions: Soften cream cheese, mix with mayo, sour cream, sugar & vanilla.
Toss in grapes & nuts and coat well.
Chill & serve.

title: olive wreath mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat pineapple syrup to a boil.
Add to lime jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
When jello begins to thicken, add pineapple, cheese, pimento, celery, nuts and salt. Fold in whipped cream.

title: green bean and turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. In a medium saucepan, combine turkey, green beans, soup and milk, mix well. Cook over medium heat until mixture is hot, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add cheese, stir until melted. Pour into ungreased 2 quart casserole. Top with prepared mashed potatoes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and melted butter. Blend in sweet potatoes.
Pour into 2 casserole dishes.
Bake until firm at 325°.

title: mrs. armstrong's strawberry cake
directions: *Mix 1 pint fresh strawberries (diced) and 1/2 cup sugar or 1 (10 ounce) package frozen strawberries (thawed) together in a glass bowl. This will make enough for both the batter and the icing.

title: pineapple coconut punch
directions: In a plastic gallon container, mix the following: powdered lemonade, sugar, cream of coconut, pineapple juice and coconut flavoring.
Blend mixture and put in a gallon container, then fill container with water until 3/4 full.
Freeze at least 24 hours. Serve partially thawed (3 hours).
Add 3 quarts 7-Up per gallon. One gallon serves 20 to 30 people.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crispy shrimp balls
directions: Combine shrimp with water chestnuts, green onions, ginger, salt, pepper, egg whites, yeast and flour in bowl; mix well. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat oil to 400° in wok.
Deep fry shrimp balls in hot oil until golden brown and crispy.
Yields 20 to 24 small appetizers.

title: taco dish
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients, starting with the beans in a rectangular pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Layer green onions, then tomatoes, then lettuce and cheese.
Sprinkle diced black olives over top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with a bag of plain nacho chips.
Great as an appetizer or a meal!

title: strawberry dip (for fruit)
directions: Mix the jam and sour cream together. Will have a purple color. Cover and place in fridge. Great for fruit dipping.

title: homemade spaghetti and meat balls
directions: In a large pot, add pureed tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, 1/4 c. sugar, small chopped onion, and salt and pepper.
Bring to almost boiling.
In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, chopped onion, salt, eggs, 2 tsp. sugar and moistened bread crumbs.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls and put in heated sauce mixture.
Cook over low/medium heat until hot and bubbly.
Turn down fire and cook on low, simmering for approximately 2 hours. Serve over your choice of spaghetti noodles.

title: civitan fruit cake cookies
directions: Dice fruit cake into 1/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
(Slices and dices best when refrigerated.)
Mix remaining ingredients and add fruit cake pieces.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spicy oven fried chicken
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk, then coat with corn meal mixture. Place chicken, skin side up in large shallow baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: egg salad magnifique
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and horseradish, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, crabmeat, celery and peppers; mix lightly.
Chill.
Fill croissants with lettuce and egg mixture.

title: smoked trout, green bean and new potato salad
directions: Toss the potatoes in a little olive oil and roast at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until just done, then cool.
Steam green beans, then cool.
Mix lemon juice, vinegar, mustard, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Slice potatoes thinly and toss with green beans, onion and dressing.
Flake the trout and toss into the salad.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook peppers and onions in 3 tablespoons Crisco until yellow. Add and fry until meat falls apart.
Stir tomatoes, rice and spices together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake, remove cover last 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peach angel dessert
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually whisk in water and corn syrup until smooth. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Cook 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved. Cool to room temperature, stirring several times. Cut angel food cake into 9 slices. Line an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 dish with the slices. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until blended. Gradually beat in confectioners sugar. Set aside 1/3 cup whipped topping for garnish. Fold remaining whipped topping into cream cheese mixture; spread over cake. Top with peaches. Pour gelatin mixture over peaches. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Cut into squares. Top each piece with about 1 teaspoon of reserved topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter with salt and pepper. When chicken is done, add broccoli and carrots. Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until lightly brown.
Add ham and shrimp. Cook just until ham is lightly brown or shrimp are light pink. Drain tomatoes, measuring juice.
Add water to juice to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Add the liquid, tomatoes, salt, thyme, bay leaf, parsley and sugar to mixture in skillet.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend ingredients and add chopped meat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: diet shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with Sweet 'N Low and set aside.
Cook 7-Up and cornstarch until clear.
Stir until thick.
Add one small box of sugar-free strawberry jello.
Cool and add 8 to 10 packages of Sweet 'N Low or to suit taste.
Add strawberries and pour into graham crackers or baked crust.
Cool and add Cool Whip.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar and let boil 6 minutes on low heat, stirring almost constantly, because it is easy to scorch.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except the wieners.
Do not brown ground beef separately.
Simmer and stir until thick.
Add the wieners.
Stir and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve on hot dogs with mustard and onions.

title: mushroom delite
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until almost done. Add mushrooms. Set aside.
Place 1/3 of bread in buttered dish, spoon half of veggies over bread, layer 1/3 bread and 1/2 veggies. Top with remaining bread.
Pour egg and milk mixture over all. Spoon soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add reserved pineapple juice.
Bake in 1 or 2 pans and, when done, split layers.

title: hash
directions: Cook beef and onion, salt and pepper covered with water in pressure cooker for 1 hour.
When cooked to pieces, add vinegar, catsup and chili powder.
Cook on low heat until thickens, stirring so it won't stick.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Put about 2 tablespoons of prepared dressing in the center of 2 slices of turkey and roll the turkey around dressing.
Place in baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Continue until all meat is used.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus. Form layers of asparagus, undiluted soup, chopped eggs, butter and cracker crumbs until all around edges of baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 300° in oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: royal hashed potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add potatoes and onions. Season with salt, then add milk.
Let cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom.
Fold over like an omelet and serve garnished with parsley.

title: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits ii(a copykat recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms. Drop by spoonfuls
onto an ungreased cooking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Mix butter and garlic powder. Brush mixture over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Beat egg.
Add oil and beat.
Add rest of ingredients and beat.
You can marinate chicken in sauce, or you can just dip in sauce and barbecue.
Each time you turn, dip in sauce until done or nice and brown.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in blueberries.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until set.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill several hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Remove paper from cans of Eagle Brand milk.
Place unopened cans in pot of water covered and boil for 2 hours.
Remove cans from water and cool completely (do not open).
When cool, open and spread 1 1/2 to 2 cans of the caramelized Eagle Brand milk over graham cracker pie crust.
Slice 3 bananas and layer over caramelized milk.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Chill and serve.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl. Pour mixture in pan of melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour can of pie filling across mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 25-30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sausage scramble
directions: Saute green peppers and onions. Add sausage. Cut into tiny pieces. Add hash browns. Cook until tender. Add Egg Beaters and finish cooking. When done, place on plates and sprinkle with cheese.

title: peach rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and sugar. Cook over medium heat in 3-quart saucepan until thick and creamy, about 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often. Add vanilla. Pour into serving dish. Heat honey, butter, lemon juice, lemon peel, nutmeg and salt. Stir in drained peaches. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Spoon over pudding. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add can of Eagle Brand milk slowly to Dream Whip, then add lemon juice slowly to mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Pour cherry filling on top of pie.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: berries 'n cream brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package directions using a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cool completely on a wire rack. Spread whipped topping over brownies. Arrange strawberries, cut side down, over top. Drizzle with chocolate topping. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown hamburger (ground meat) and onion in small amount of fat.
Add flour, then water and tomato sauce.
Season with chili powder, salt and garlic.
Cover and let simmer at least 30 minutes.
(If too thick, add a little more water.)
When this is done, arrange 1/2 package of Fritos in a baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese over the layer of Fritos, then add cooked chili. Arrange the rest of the Fritos on top of the chili, then add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: toffee cream crunch
directions: Before unwraping, crush English toffee. As directed, prepare topping mix. Fold together. On serving plate, halve ladyfingers, place 1/2 row upside-down on platter. Spoon 1/3 of topping over ladyfinger row. Repeat with ladyfingers right side up, ending with ladyfingers. Refrigerate and slice into servings.

title: gourmet crab ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in cold water.
Beat into cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate at least 4 hours or more.
To serve, turn on a plate and garnish with parsley.
Serve with "Escort" crackers or crackers of your choice.

title: brunch sausage casserole
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle cheese and sausage evenly over the bread.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper together.
Pour mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: old fashion pot roast
directions: Put roast in pan and brown; drain fat.
Place rest of ingredients with roast.
Bake in oven at 350° until meat is tender.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat butter, sugar and egg together until fluffy.
Add chopped apples and sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Bake in greased 8 or 9-inch square pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good served hot with pudding sauce.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and undiluted soup.
Add a spoonful of water if too thick.
Pour in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Slightly cook spinach and drain well (no salt added).
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Form into balls approximately 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
(Balls can also be frozen.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or 350° for 35 minutes if frozen.
Makes 50 to 60 balls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients listed.
Add raisins and nuts as desired. Pour into lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan. Freezes well.

title: homemade vegetable soup(or just good stew beef)
directions: Note:
This is to be cooked in pressure cooker, 2, 4 or 6-quart size.

title: mock strawberry dessert
directions: Grind vanilla wafers coarsely in food chopper.
Pat half of the crumbs firmly on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream powdered sugar, butter and egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread over wafers carefully with knife or teaspoon.
This is a little difficult and must be done carefully.
Mix together cranberries, apples, pineapple and sugar.
Spread this over the mixture.
Whip half pint of cream and add 1 tablespoon powdered sugar.
Spread over other ingredients and sprinkle remainder of the wafer crumbs on top.
The dessert can be kept several days in a refrigerator.

title: zucchini apricot jam
directions: Wash and dry the lemons carefully and then grate the rind from each thinly.
Squeeze out all the juice.
Put the rind and juice in a saucepan. Add the eggs previously beaten with the margarine and sugar.
Heat the mixture, stirring it well with a wooden spoon, until the sugar dissolves and the curd thickens.
Remove pan from heat.
Pour curd into hot sterilized jars and cover at once.

title: the big cookie
directions: Mix together.
Add nuts, chips, raisins, etc.
Mix and spread into a pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs and sugar; mix them.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed beat margarine, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
At low speed beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press candies or nuts into cookies, or press with thumb and fill with jam or jelly.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: low-fat, low calorie vanilla sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; gradually stir in milk and egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium-low heat; stir constantly with a wire whisk.
Cook 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla; let cool.
Yield:
1 cup (about 16 calories per tablespoon).
Serve over pancakes with fresh raspberries or strawberries or over a fresh cobbler or fruit.

title: mashed banana cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; then remove and cool on rack.

title: butter cookies
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly into butter; use hands, if necessary.
Pinch off small pieces of mixture; roll into balls the size of large marbles. Place on cookie sheet.
Make a small depression in each; fill this with some tart jelly or preserves.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Watch carefully, as they burn easily.
(Cooking time:
20 to 30 minutes.) Yields 24.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream both sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into logs on wax paper to cool in refrigerator until firm.
Remove, cut into 1/4-inch slices and bake on ungreased pan until edges are light brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees. Place popped corn in large roasting pan; let stand in oven while preparing glaze. In medium saucepan combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Without stirring, boil 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla. Pour over warm popcorn; toss to coat well. Bake 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool, stirring frequently. Store in tightly-covered container. Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients
well
and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° until brown.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Add flour and egg; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture over sugared peaches.
Don't try to cover every peach, just drop spoonfuls randomly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Great with vanilla ice cream!

title: divine make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Beat the cream cheese.
Add butter.
Put in potatoes and mash by hand.
Put in mixer and add remaining ingredients.
Put into casserole and top with butter and paprika or cheese. Bake.

title: bacon ranch dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate until cool.
Serve with assorted cut-up vegetables or chips.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, crushed pineapple.
Cook stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups sugar, salt and eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla. Place cooled pineapple mixture in unbaked pie crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture over it.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° for 50 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Use fruit juice and water to make 6 cups of liquid.
Heat until boiling.
Dissolve jello.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture until dissolved.
Dip bananas in pineapple juice to prevent darkening.
Add a pinch of salt, pineapple chunks and bananas to cooled jello.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook and stir sugar, cornstarch and water; stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Place strawberries in pie crust, then pour mixture over them.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix together egg, milk, salad oil and pineapple with juice. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, then add to egg mixture.
Stir together just until moistened. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In 2 quart casserole dish combine sugar, Karo, salt and water. Stir.
Microwave
on
High
for
minutes, stirring every
5 minutes.
Beat
egg
whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites slowly.
(Be very careful as syrup is extremely
hot.) Beat 12 minutes.
Fold in pecans and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: taco salad bowl
directions: In medium skillet, saute chuck and garlic until meat is browned; drain excess fat.
Add green chilies, tomatoes, salt and pepper; mix well.
Cook over low heat uncovered about 30 minutes. Just before serving, in large chilled salad bowl, arrange lettuce, cheese, corn chips and green onions with cooked meat mixture.
Toss lightly until well combined.
Garnish with chopped tomato.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: evelyn's molasses cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Beat in molasses.
Combine vinegar and milk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Chill.

title: taylor family lemon pecan cake
directions: Grease and flour large Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract.
Mix baking powder and flour together.
Add flour a little at a time to creamed mixture, until well blended.
Fold in other ingredients.
Bake in 275° to 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients together, except chopped meat.
Once ingredients are mixed well, then add chopped meat.
Pour into a 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 3-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Add a ladle full of gravy.
Cook for another 10 minutes.

title: coconut pies
directions: Put egg yolks and next 3 ingredients in double boiler.
Boil until thick.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Mix well and pour into two already baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stand to a peak.
Add sugar to taste or 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread on pies. Bake at 350° until crust is light brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and margarine. Bring to a boil and turn off heat.
Cut shortening into flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk all at once.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Pare and core apples.
Slice and sprinkle with additional sugar (brown or white) and spice.
Arrange on a square piece of dough.
Dot with butter and fold corners to center.
Place upside-down in greased baking dish.
Pour hot syrup between dumplings.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Cook sweet potatoes until done.
Peel when cooled.
In a large mixing bowl, mix in sweet potatoes and brown sugar.
Blend in eggs and sugar.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: bob's fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill in refrigerator 4 hours.

title: french fried potato salad
directions: Pour the 4 cups of water into a large saucepan; bring to a full, rolling boil.
Carefully drop frozen potatoes into water. Remove from heat immediately; cover and let stand 4 to 5 minutes. Drain potatoes at once.
Spread on paper toweling.
Cut up any large pieces.
Sprinkle potatoes with the salt; cool.
In bowl combine eggs, radishes, celery, green onion and snipped parsley. Add mayonnaise and vinegar.
Add potatoes and toss mixture gently. Chill.
Garnish with parsley and radish roses, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan crusted artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, cook three minutes. Add spinach - cook 3 to 5 minutes - stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in Artichoke, cream cheese, mayonnaise, cheddar cheese, parmesan cheese and hot sauce. Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2 Quart casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Top with pecans and bake 10 minutes more.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: pecan pie a la kent
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, creaming constantly, then add syrup.
Whip the salt and eggs until light and fluffy.
Blend into sugar and syrup mixture.
Add vanilla and nut meats.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; don't forget to bake on cookie sheet.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: onion-cheese pie
directions: Cover bottom of pastry shell with onion, then cheese.
Mix flour into small amount of milk, then stir in remaining milk. Add flour and milk mixture, salt, pepper and butter to eggs.
Mix well; pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until nicely browned and set.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, onions, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, chili pepper and milk and mix well.
Make into balls and cook in oil until brown.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, sugar, vinegar and tomato sauce.
Bring ingredients to a boil and pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: layered taco dip(appetizer)
directions: Spread refried beans on the bottom of a flat casserole dish. Next, you mix cream cheese and sour cream together until smooth and layer it on top of the refried beans.
Next, you take the green chiles and layer that on top of the cream cheese/sour cream mixture. Take package of shredded Cheddar cheese and layer that on top of chiles.
Now you take shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and black olives and layer individually.
Now you pour the sauce on the top of all the ingredients.
Serve with nacho chips. Enjoy!

title: baked teriyaki chicken
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken or turkey on top.
Put garlic salt or powder on chicken.
Pour remaining ingredients on top of chicken.
Throw cut up mushrooms on top of chicken.
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: carrot pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 2 loaf pans.
Mix cake mix, sour cream, brown sugar, allspice, cinnamon and eggs until well blended.
Fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans. Bake about 50 minutes.
(May use a Bundt pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Boil until brown streaks appear when you stir.
While cake is still hot in pan, pour this sauce over it.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water; let stand for 10 minutes.
Blend cottage cheese and 1 tablespoon butter in large bowl.
Mix sugar, salt and soda; add to cheese mixture.
Add onion, dill seed, egg and yeast mixture; beat well. Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Cover; let rise in warm place for about 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Stir down.

title: cornflake pecan dreams
directions: Beat room temperature oleo until very light. Add sugar and beat. Add vanilla, flour, soda and cream of tartar, then cornflakes and pecans. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; flatten with a fork to 2-inches in diameter. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 60.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, cornflakes, salt and pepper. Form into 6 to 8 patties.
Roll in flour and brown in hot oil. Place patties in baking dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add next 2 ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix next 5 ingredients.
Mix butter and flour mixtures together.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Make into golf ball size balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crabmeat broccoli pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in butter (as you would for a pie crust).
Add milk and chives.
Stir and mix until dough forms a ball.
Pat into a 9-inch pie plate, covering bottom and sides. Cook broccoli and drain well.
Place broccoli in pie crust. Combine remaining ingredients, except paprika, and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown and heated through completely.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine and chill several hours before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, salt, cinnamon or nutmeg and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Place in a very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Decrease heat to 325° and cook until set, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour after sifting (by spoonful).
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll in 1-inch balls, then roll into powdered sugar and bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
They are best when soft and chewy.

title: christmas bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and spice.
Cool milk to lukewarm; add yeast.
Blend milk mixture with 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Add creamed mixture and remaining flour; mix until smooth.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Divide into three equal portions.
Put two portions aside.
Divide remaining portion into three equal pieces.
Shape each piece into a rope and then braid.
Tuck ends under and place on greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining two portions.
Let rise until almost doubled in bulk.
Brush tops of loaves with egg yolk, mixed with a little bit of water.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with plenty of butter.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Arrange washed and dried chicken in a greased casserole dish. Season with salt and pepper; add water.
Place in oven and cook until tender.
Remove from oven.
Spread on barbecue sauce.
Cover and return to oven and cook 10 minutes.

title: swedish rye bread(for bread machine)
directions: Makes 1 large loaf.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet
potatoes until tender and peel them.
Slice one into the
bottom
of
a casserole dish.
Peel and slice an apple over
the
potato
layer.
Add 1/4 cup nuts and sprinkle with 1/2 cup
brown
sugar
and
cinnamon.
Slice potato over this, then another
apple.
Repeat
until everything is used. Slice butter on top
and bake at 375° until apples are tender or about 30 minutes.
Serves
This
dish is a favorite at Thanksgiving.

title: microwave basic white sauce
directions: In 1-quart glass bowl, place butter, flour and salt. Microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave at High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring every minute until thick and bubbly.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and lay it aside.
Fry diced onion in bacon grease. Bring to a boil the vinegar, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Add bacon grease.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in a skillet.
Drain. Add pimento and mushroom soup.
Stir well.
Pour half of mixture in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Pour rest of mixture on top of this and add cheese on top.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cook at 450° until mixture bubbles through Tater Tots.

title: emily peacock's white spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken (boil).
Pull meat from chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Mix with spaghetti.
Melt Velveeta cheese, mushroom soup and pimento. Combine with spaghetti until done.

title: easy breakfast quiche
directions: In large bowl, beat together eggs and cream cheese until blended (will be slightly lumpy).
Stir in bacon, onions and shredded cheese.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
In a 10-inch pie plate, layer the crescent rolls so the entire plate is covered.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake at 375° until set to desired consistency.
Will serve 6 to 8, depending on how large you slice it!

title: skillet festive chicken
directions: Rinse chicken well.
In bag, combine flour, salt and chili powder.
Shake chicken, a few pieces at a time, in flour mixture to coat.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except hot cooked rice. Mix well.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken.
Simmer covered 40 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: Cut down on amount of smoke if you desire!

title: layered casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, beef, bacon, cheese, onion and pepper in casserole dish.
Spread tomato soup across top.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Cover with foil before cooking.
If desired may precook potatoes, beef and bacon before placing in dish.
Drain fat.
Then layer and will cook in 30 minutes at 350°.

title: neptune shrimp salad
directions: Combine all, chill and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Refrigerate (can be frozen).
Add Sprite and ginger ale when ready to serve.
Great for large parties or weddings.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Defrost Cool Whip (easier to spread).
Press crushed crackers with melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk; fold in ice cream.
Spread over crackers evenly.
Spread Cool Whip over mixture.
Grate Heath bar on top for decoration. Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pistachio pudding and milk; mix well.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate and serve in a couple of hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Process Oreos to crumbs through a food processor.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar until smooth.
Combine pudding and milk.
Combine cream cheese mixture, pudding and Cool Whip.
Layer mix alternately.
Begin with Oreos and end with Oreos in 12-inch plastic flowerpot.
Top with silk flowers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put in crock-pot and let cool on low.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Flatten one roll at a time and line a muffin tin with it.
Mix the meat, sauce and onions.
Spoon into muffin tin lined with roll, about 1 tablespoon each.
Sprinkle cheese on top of each. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Crumble, cook and drain hot sausage.
Mix with rest of ingredients and heat in crock pot.
Serve with large tortilla chips.
Double this recipe for large crowds.

title: ham-cheddar quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell 5 minutes.
In layers cover pastry with half the cheese, ham and onion.
Repeat the layers.
In medium bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper. Gradually pour in milk, blending well.
Add eggs.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: green cheese omelet
directions: Break eggs in bowl.
Add food coloring.
Whip until fluffy. Pour into greased pan.
Cook until almost done.
Add cheese.
Fold in half and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan.
Mix well.
Bake in a large iron skillet or in loaf pan until done at 375°.

title: broccoli with mornay sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water for 5 minutes or until almost tender.
Refresh under cold water.
Drain well.
In medium saucepan, saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir constantly over low heat for 1 minute.
Add milk, whisking constantly.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Mixture will thicken.
Stir in Swiss cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Coat bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with sauce.
Arrange broccoli over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over broccoli.
Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: molasses pecan cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add molasses; mix well.
Combine creamed mixture and dry ingredients.
Add nuts; blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, broth, onion, chili peppers and seasonings together.
In casserole, place layers of tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger; drain and prepare taco mix according to package directions.
Mix together with the next 6 ingredients. Add the Doritos when ready to eat.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season chops with pepper and garlic salt and brown.
Place chops in baking dish and put a slice of onion on each chop.
Mix together soup, ketchup and sauce and pour mixture over pork chops. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly and browned.
Combine sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Add water.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: fried carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots in cold water for about 5 minutes.
In a skillet add butter and oil.
When mixture is hot add onion and carrots.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Cook for 10 more minutes.
Add 1 cup of water; cook for 10 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Serve.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in a bowl and blend really well. In a separate bowl, combine the next 5 ingredients.
Combine wet and dry mixtures and fold together gently until mixed.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: red cabbage 'n' apples
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine; stir in lemon juice, sugar, water, caraway, and salt.
Add cabbage and apples; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25-30 minutes.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Mash.
Add salt and rest of ingredients and stir until well blended.

title: rotel ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large saucepan, cook pepper and onion in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes. Add soups, Ro-Tel, and chicken, stirring until well blended. In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, alternately layer tortillas, soup mixture and cheese, repeating for three layers. Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbling. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter-carrot cookies
directions: Mix oats, flour and baking soda in bowl.
Cream butter and peanut butter in mixer bowl.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat until light.
Add egg and milk; mix well.
Stir in oats mixture 1/4 at a time.
Stir in carrot and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and chilies.
Stir.
Microwave until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: mom's dirt
directions: You will need 8 to 10 plastic or paper cups.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch, add pineapple. Cook on medium heat, stirring till thick and clear. Cool.
Combine cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt, stir until smooth and well blended.

Add eggs one at a time, stirring well after each egg, blend in milk and vanilla. Spread cooled pineapple mixture over bottom pie shell. Pour cream mixture over pineapple. Sprinkle with nuts or nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 50 minutes or until brown and center is set.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix together salad dressing, dill weed, oil and garlic powder.
Add crackers.
Coat well with this mixture. Place on cookie sheet and bake for about 20 minutes.
After cooling put in airtight container.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Dissolve cocoa in hot water; add to preceding.
Dissolve soda and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice the onions.
Brown in pan with 1 stick of oleo.
Add sugar and flour.
Put in a 4-quart crock-pot.
Add enough water to fill.
Add beef bouillon cubes.
Add an additional 1/2 stick of oleo.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Add croutons and cheese when serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix well. Shape into ball and roll in pecans. Wrap in foil and refrigerate for one hour before serving.

title: chocolate chisters
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla; beat until fluffy and add chocolate and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until delicately brown.
Makes about 24 to 28 cookies.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in flour and pepper. Add milk all at once and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; add cheese and mayonnaise; stir until cheese melts. Combine potatoes and ham with sauce. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with small amount of water until tender. Drain well. In saucepan melt cheese, milk and soup. In buttered casserole dish, sprinkle half the stuffing and seasoning packet. Add squash and onion, and then add milk mixture. Sprinkle remaining stuffing and seasoning packet on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a pan.
Add 1/2 cup water to sugar mixture. Add rest of water and stir until it boils and thickens.
Pour a little of the hot mixture over eggs and mix. Pour eggs into hot mixture and bring to a boil. Remove from stove. Add lemon rind, juice and butter.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue. Beat 3 egg whites stiff and slowly add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Pile on pie.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Use a baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes, into baking dish. Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: buster bars
directions: Crush cookies (save 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top).
Mix with melted margarine and pat firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, using a 2 prong fork.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes as for potato salad.
Cool and set aside. Mix together sour cream, soup, margarine, grated cheese, salt, pepper and grated onion.
Mix well.
Mix gently with potatoes. Place
in large
buttered
casserole	9
x 12-inch.
Top with buttered corn flake mixture and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Top will brown nicely.

title: cucumber sweet pickles
directions: Use overripe cucumbers only!
For every pound of cucumbers, allow 3 pounds of sugar and 1 quart of vinegar.
Let the cucumbers soak overnight in salt and water, then scald them in weak soft vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil a little, then put in the cucumbers and scald them until transparent, not soft.
These pickles are for overripe cucumbers only.

title: crisp spinach salad
directions: Trim and discard the tough spinach stems.
Rinse the leaves well; dry and break into bite size pieces.
In a very large salad bowl, combine the spinach, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
In a frying pan over medium heat, fry the bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into spinach.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour juices and water into 30 cup automatic percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket of percolator and allow to go through perk cycle (about 30 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients (except potato chips) the night before. Place in 9 x 13 inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before dinner put crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Put in large casserole or 13 x 15-inch dish.
Top with crushed chips. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs and press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth and pour on crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Spread strawberry glaze and strawberries on top of Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rouladen or beef roll-ups(serves 6 or 8)
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Saute in frypan until cooked, but not crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Lay steaks out on counter. Sprinkle with tenderizer.
Turn steaks over.
Place some onion chunks or 1 green onion, cut in half, on steak and 2 pieces of bacon.
If you use the pickle, cut it in 8 sticks.
Place one on each steak.
Pepper to taste.
Roll up and tie with string. Brown in bacon drippings.
Add 1 can condensed beef broth or consomme and 1 can water.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Turn down heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Check if tender.
If not, simmer another 1/2 hour. I put mine in a Dutch oven and bake at 350° after it has been fried and the broth added.
Takes 1 1/2 hours in oven. Remove rolls.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch in a cup of water. Then add to gravy and cook until thickened and clear.
You can add some red wine instead of all water to cornstarch.
Remove string before serving. You can use minute steaks for this, too.

title: spaghetti sauce with meatballs and sausage
directions: Sauce:
Cover bottom of pan with oil.
Cook sausage slowly until barely brown.
Add salt, pepper, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Add tomato puree and water.
Stir well.
Add tomato paste and water.
Stir well. Add basil and simmer for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice for 6 servings as directed. Set aside. In a large saucepan, melt the butter.
Add onion. Cook for a few minutes.
Add broccoli, breaking apart with a fork.
Cook until tender. Add rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: johnnie's weird cake
directions: Butter pan.
Put pineapple in bottom of pan.
On top of this, put the cherry pie filling, then put cake batter on top of pineapple and pie filling.
Last, top with melted butter; spread evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
It will bubble around edges.
This is a quick dessert.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, combine cheese, flour, salt, pepper and dry milk.
Add scalded milk; add spinach and add eggs and onion.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add apples and raisins.
Turn into 8-inch square baking dish.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread cherries on top.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook together hamburger, bacon and onions; drain.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, salt, mustard and catsup.
Drain all the beans slightly.
Add to meat mixture and mix thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole dish at 350°.

title: almond bark clusters
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Melt almond bark and pour over the dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by the teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: raisin pie
directions: Soak raisins 3 hours.
Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Add seasoning, raisins and liquid.
Cook over hot water for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
When mixture is cool, empty into dough lined pie dish.
Cover with strips of dough, crisscrossed. Then bake until browned.

title: christmas punch
directions: Bring sugar and 4
1/2 c. water to boil and let cool.

Then boil 2 cups water and dissolve jello. Let cool. Mix together. Mix all together and put in plastic containers and freeze. When ready to serve mix about 1 quart punch mix to 1/3 bottle callins mix.

title: vanilla glaze
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Spread on top of cake or cookies.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt margarine (or butter).
Add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Add broth, pepper and potatoes; heat to a boil.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat.
In blender, place half broth mixture and 3/4 cup milk. Cover and blend until smooth.
Repeat with remaining broth and milk.
Return to pan.
Over medium heat, heat thoroughly.
Garnish with onion.

title: welsh rarebit with beans
directions: Heat beans and cheese together until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly hot.
Serve over toast garnished with crisp bacon.

title: cream cheese-chocolate chip tube cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese in large mixing bowl with electric mixer.
Beat in sugar gradually, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir flour with baking powder and salt.
Stir with vanilla and chocolate chips into butter mixture.
Bake in greased 8-inch tube pan in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or until top springs back when lightly touched with finger.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out onto rack and cool completely.
Glaze if you wish or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Cut the asparagus in small pieces.
Dissolve the lime jello in one cup boiling water.
When cooled, add all other ingredients. Pour into a mold or pan and allow to set until firm.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Top with mayonnaise or sour cream, if desired.

title: breadcrumb pie
directions: Put in single crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Serve with dab of whipped cream!

title: buttermilk refrigerator pancakes
directions: Add soda, sugar and salt to buttermilk.
Sift baking powder and flour into this.
Add yeast.
Stir in oil, cream and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and allow batter to stand at room temperature to activate the yeast.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Store in a 3 pound coffee can.
It will keep 10 days or longer.
Use from it as you wish.

title: williamsburg turkey soup
directions: Place turkey carcass and water in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove carcass from broth; pick meat from bones.
Set broth and meat aside. Measure broth; add water to broth, if necessary, to measure 3 quarts.
Heat butter in Dutch oven.
Add flour; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
(Roux will be a very light color.)

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine in large bowl.

title: incredible egg-macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions.
Add other ingredients, except the egg slices.
Mix lightly.
Use additional mayonnaise, if needed.
Garnish with egg slices.
Chill.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and discard liquid.
Combine celery, onion and relish; stir in seasonings and mix thoroughly with beans. Chill and serve on crisp lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook bacon; use drippings.
Add soup, sugar, garlic, milk and vinegar.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: italian beef
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Put in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with dry spaghetti mix.
Cut stems off pepperoncinis; pour pepperoncinis and juice over roast.
Cook on low all day.
Ready when you get home from work!
Serve on hoagie buns.

title: quick corn biscuits
directions: Melt butter on a sided cookie sheet.
Mix Bisquick and corn. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Turn each biscuit so that it is coated with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with sauce.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small bits; saute, but do not crisp.
Saute chopped onions with bacon, then add celery and saute.
Add juice from clams and water to make 2 cups.
Add chopped potatoes and chopped carrots and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped clams and cook 5 minutes.
Add butter or oleo. Add 2 cans Jake's soup if you need a larger amount.
Just before serving, add cream and milk to desired consistency.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt together and let stand one hour.
Then add;
celery, green peppers, carrots and onions, chopped fine, as much of each as you like.
Combine the following in a saucepan: vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed, and mustard seed.
Boil for one minute then cool to room temperature.
Pour over chopped vegetables, mixing well.
Pack into freezer containers.
To use just thaw and serve.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given (dry ingredients sifted together).
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet and press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet until firm enough to remove.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put 2 cups bran in a large bowl and pour boiling water over. Let stand for a few minutes.
Mix shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: bailey's cream
directions: Mix all in blender; let "age" in refrigerator for 1 week. After using, leave in fridge.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces in a 9 x 12-inch dish. Layer the next 6 ingredients in order given.
Next, mix mayo and sugar; spread on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill for 24 hours before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, pineapple and pecans together. Add Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell and chill in refrigerator until set, about 30 to 45 minutes before serving. Keep in refrigerator.

title: lemon slush
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and freeze overnight.
When ready to serve, thaw slightly and add 2 bottles of ginger ale.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and 2 beaten egg yolks.
Slowly add juice of lemons.
Stir by hand until it starts to thicken.
Line a pie plate with vanilla wafer bottom and sides.
Pour lemon filling in pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and about 4 or 5 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Pour on pie and bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: fiesta omelet(makes 2 servings)
directions: In 8-inch nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, cook pepper, mushrooms and onion in 2 teaspoons margarine until tender. Remove from skillet; set aside.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put in oven to melt butter.
After butter is melted, remove from oven.
In large mixing bowl beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese, drained spinach and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
These freeze very well.
They can be reheated frozen at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Start this recipe in the late afternoon.
Bring sugar and 2 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in shortening.
Let stand to cool.
Soften yeast in warm water. Combine yeast, salt and eggs with cooked mixture in mixer bowl. Add 4 cups flour, beating well.
Add 2 cups flour; beat by hand. Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Roll on floured surface. Spread with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Roll up; cut into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Place in buttered 10 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise, uncovered, in cold oven overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cut meat in bite size portions.
Mix together chicken, soup, Veg-All, chicken broth and garlic powder. Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: ham and cheese finger sandwiches
directions: Slice lengthwise tea rolls; place layer of ham and Swiss cheese in middle.
Mix margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Pour over rolls and let stand 15 minutes.
Heat at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir sauce.
Pour into casserole dish.
Combine potatoes and cheese, spoon over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quicky peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a long cake pan in a 350° oven.
Take out of oven; pour dry cake mix on top of melted oleo (completely cover bottom of pan).
Then pour a large can of peaches over cake mix. Add a large can of water, cinnamon and sugar.
Stir a little bit and put in oven at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: cranberry salad for 50
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and stir well to break up canned cranberries.
Chill.

title: baked fish
directions: Melt butter in baking dish and roll cut up fish, coating all sides.
Mix seasonings with crackers and roll fish.
Place in baking dish and top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until fish flakes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set at 350°. Cover with egg whites.

title: beef pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Add meat and brown.
Remove to serving dish.
Add onion and pepper slices to skillet and cool until tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and soy sauce.
Add sugar, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour into skillet with vegetables, stirring until sauce is thickened and clear.
Add meat and cook several minutes longer or until heated through. Serve over hot rice.

title: scotch broth
directions: Place meat and water in a large saucepan.
Bring to the boil and add beans and peas, previously soaked.
Cook for 30 minutes. Add barley, salt, pepper, parsnip, onion and part of the carrot and turnip cut into small pieces and the remainder of the carrot and turnip cut into large pieces.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Half an hour before serving, add the cabbage (shredded), the leeks cut into halves and the parsley (chopped).
Serve the mutton with the larger pieces of vegetables and some of the liquor and serve with the remainder separately as broth.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain well.
Cut up stewed tomatoes into smaller pieces and put in large pot.
Add tomato paste and browned ground beef.
Stir and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken dish
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/4-inch baking dish.
Place cooked chicken on top of broccoli, sprinkle with almonds.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and pour over entire dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until soup mixture bubbles up.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix water, gelatin mix and puddings together in saucepan and bring to a boil until it starts to thicken.
Let cool; add Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: two crust lemon pie
directions: Cut lemon in thin slices.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour, butter and milk.
Place thin slices of lemon in pan lined with unbaked crust. Pour other mixture over lemon.
Put on top crust and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in hot water.
Beat together the soup, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add the gelatin water.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and pour into one large or two small molds. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or cut up vegetables.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugars in large bowl.
Add peanut butter and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and vanilla and mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press with floured fork to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and top with corn flakes and 1 stick of melted butter; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: tin can ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1-pound coffee can with tight fitting lid.
Place lid on can.
Place can with ingredients inside a Number 10 can with tight fitting plastic lid (larger coffee can). Pack larger can with crushed ice around smaller can.
Pour at least 3/4 cup rock salt evenly over ice.
Place lid on the Number 10 can.
Roll back and forth on a table or sidewalk for 10 minutes.
Open outer can.
Remove inner can with ingredients. Remove lid; use a rubber spatula to stir up mixture and scrape sides of can.
Replace lid.
Drain ice water from larger can. Insert smaller can; pack with more ice and salt.
Roll back and forth for 5 more minutes.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with a slice of cheese. Arrange mushrooms over the cheese.
Mix the soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix over the top and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Coat Neufchatel cheese cubes with sesame seed; chill.
In large skillet or wok, stir-fry vegetables in oleo and seasonings until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.
Add Neufchatel cheese to vegetables; mix lightly.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip cream until peaks form.
Carefully fold whipped cream into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Gradually fold in cold water and vanilla.
Sift flour, measure and sift with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Carefully fold into cream mixture.
Pour into pan that has been lightly greased and floured.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is a delicious white cake.

title: potato soup
directions: In
a
large
soup pot saute onion, celery and carrots. Add seasonings	to
taste.
Fill
pot 1/2 full of water.
Add potatoes that
were peeled and chopped, after water starts to boil.
Add chicken
broth.
Cook
until
potatoes
are almost tender.	Add canned
milk
and cheese.
Slightly mash some of the
potatoes. Cook
until cheese melts and potatoes are done but not mushy. Enjoy with cornbread!

title: ore-ida potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Place in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat salt and eggs with fork.
Heat oil very hot.
Pour in egg mixture; cook.
Stir constantly until eggs are size of peas. Reduce heat to low.
Push eggs to one side of skillet; gently stir rice with 2 tablespoons oil until rice is coated.
Add bacon and soy sauce; stir and heat.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Add 1 can mushrooms (optional).

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add slowly flour, egg and flavoring mixture.
Beat real good, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt (set aside).
Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Beat well and add flour mixture alternating with eggnog beginning with flour mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely. Makes 1 loaf.

title: tomato cheese whirls
directions: Sift
together
flour, soda and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture
resembles
fine
crumbs. Add tomato juice; mix only until
dry
ingredients
are moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board. Roll out 1/4 inch thick into rectangle. Spread dough
with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Roll up like jelly roll, starting from longer side.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place
cut
side down on baking sheet which has
been greased.
Bake
in
preheated
oven
at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: ripe tomato salad
directions: Mix all together and put in jars.
Cover with vinegar.
Will keep for months in refrigerator.
It is very good over beans or salad or can be frozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar real well.
Add flour and eggs alternately, ending with flour.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven set at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
Test at the end of 1 hour; add 20 minutes.

title: french fried zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini
in half crosswise.
Cut each half into 8 strips.
Dip zucchini in batter made with pancake mix, vinegar and water. Shake off excess.
Cook in a depth of 2 to 3-inches of oil in a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan, heated to 350°.
Fry zucchini until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve immediately. Yields about 6 appetizer servings.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: If turkey is frozen, soak in cold water overnight in cool place.
Take out of water; let drain about 30 minutes.
Rub 3 sticks of butter over turkey inside and out and salt.
Place apples inside turkey.
Line roaster pan 2 ways with tinfoil to seal turkey tightly.
Place turkey and 4 quarts water in roaster.
Seal and bake 5 hours at 350°.
Mix eggs, sage, bread and onions.
Add broth from turkey to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until soft crust forms on top.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples in pastry lined pie plate.
Mix together cornstarch, cinnamon and apple juice in a saucepan.
Stir constantly while bringing mixture to a boil.
When it goes from cloudy to clear, stir in butter (if desired).
Pour over sliced apples.
Cover with top pastry and seal.
Cut slits in top; place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in vanilla and margarine; add sugar and syrup. Fold in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and egg.
Stir in pineapple along with its juice.
Pour into ovenproof casserole. Top with bread cubes and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, combine rice, soup and water. Layer meat over rice mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yummy pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar and beat after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on well greased baking sheet. Bake at 250 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool on sheet before removing.
Store in air tight container.

title: easy cherry pudding
directions: In 9-inch square pan, melt butter or margarine.
In bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir.
Pour undrained cherries over batter; do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over cherries; do not stir. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(May use other canned fruits in their own natural juices.)

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch oblong greased casserole pan, place a large can of boned chicken.
In a saucepan, mix the cream of chicken soup and milk; stir until well mixed.
Do not heat milk.
Pour over chicken.
On top, add croutons; press down a little.
Dot with margarine or butter.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
After 15 minutes, press stuffing down again.

title: glaze for pastry
directions: Mix together and pour over pastry.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box. Add 1 1/2 oz coconut to batter, while cake is baking, mix can of cream of coconut and sweetened milk together. As soon as you remove the cake from oven, poke holes in the cake with a wooden spoon handle. Pour the coconut and sweetened milk mixture over the cake and top with cool whip. Sprinkle coconut on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and slice apples into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and crumble on top of apples.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Top will be golden brown when done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients with spinach. Shape into small balls (size of walnut).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: paella(from the world's 100 best recipes roland goock)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add pork and chicken; cook for 15 minutes or until chicken is browned on all sides.
Add onion, garlic and ham; cook for 5 minutes longer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add broth mixed with saffron and bay leaf.
Cook 30 minutes, remove bay leaf and add rice.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper; grease.
In small bowl, beat eggs about 5 minutes, or until very thick and lemon color.
Pour eggs in larger mixing bowl. Gradually beat in sugar, water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour. Beat just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan, spreading batter to corners.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Add butter.
Drop by tablespoon on oiled griddle.
Cook until done.

title: creamy bac'n pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Rinse and drain.
In small bowl, combine Miracle light, vinegar, bacon pieces and Season-All with a whisk.
In large bowl, toss pasta with mayonnaise mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: dee's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake well.

title: 4th of july chocolate fudge sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the water, shortening, oleo and cocoa.
Cool. Add soda to buttermilk. Add to mixture the flour, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add buttermilk, then eggs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: savory skillet lasagna
directions: Cook sausage and onion over medium-high heat in skillet until crumbled and no longer pink. Drain. Blend in tomatoes and paste. Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: cinnamon punch
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together in a large boiler.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir thoroughly.
Serve hot or cold. Makes about 5 quarts.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add to liquids.
Mix well and fold in apples and nuts.
May add milk if mixture is too stiff.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into little balls.
Bake at 350° until light brown. Remove from oven and let cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: asian chicken
directions: Heat oil in large heavy skillet and brown chicken well on all sides; when chicken is almost done, add garlic and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium-high heat until chicken is done and sauce has been reduced somewhat.
This will not take long (less than 10 minutes).
Watch very carefully so that the sauce does not burn or boil away.
There should be a quantity of sauce left to serve with the chicken and the chicken should appear slightly glazed.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: irish scones
directions: Rub margarine into flour.
Add sugar and raisins.
Beat egg and milk; add to mixture and knead into a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into rings.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add garlic and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, cream, cheese and milk; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Prepare noodles.
Add noodles and shrimp to sauteed mixture.
If appears dry, add more evaporated milk. Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly.

title: sweet & spicy mustard
directions: In blender, beat eggs and gradually add vinegar.
Add all other ingredients except butter.
Put in a double boiler or regular non-stick pan and cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter to hot mixture and stir until melted.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
