title: smoked fish
directions: Season fish for about 12 hours with Toni seasoning.
Put on smoker or grill and cook until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of pan and place apples in pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes until topping is golden brown.

title: choco-dot cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, oleo, vanilla and eggs in large bowl. Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in candies and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased sheet. Press 3 or 4 candies in each cookie (if desired).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: brie in round bread
directions: Mix the mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Taste for flavor and add more cheese, if needed.
Spread the mixture on bread and toast under the broiler until melted and slightly brown.
Cut bread into quarters and serve immediately.
Any kind of bread will do.
If Italian/French loaves, cut into thin slices.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Shred shrimp and save some of the juice.
Grate the onions and mix with shrimp, sauces and some of the juice.
Mash until a firm but spreadable consistency.
Flavor will increase if let stand for a while.

title: punch
directions: Make syrup of water and sugar.
Add tea and juices to syrup. Mix as served 1/3 punch base and 2/3 ginger ale.

title: cinnamon-raisin muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, Cream of Wheat, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg, margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients, just until moistened.
Stir in raisins.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Put flour in wooden dough bowl.
In center, make a hole.
Put shortening in hole; add milk slowly, working in shortening and milk with your fingers.
Continue adding milk until shortening is worked in.
Knead dough until it makes a well floured, easy to handle dough.
Pinch off small pieces and roll in the palm of hands.
Place on baking sheet; using your hands, press dough flat. Bake at 450° until bottoms are brown.
Place under broiler until top browns.
Serve with homemade butter and homemade syrup. Makes about 12, depending on size.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut wing in half at joint.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. In deep fryer, place oil and heat to high temperature.
Add half the wings and cook (about 10 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
When brown and crisp, remove and drain.
Repeat until all wings are cooked.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add hot sauce and vinegar. Pour over cooked wings.
Serve with Bleu cheese dressing and celery.

title: corn casserole(8 to 12 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl (save a little butter). Crumble saltines and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and drizzle butter over all.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until set in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: texas cake
directions: Cream together flour, sugar, salt, vanilla, eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Meanwhile, bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add boiling liquid to first mixture.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: where is the fat? chocolate sauce(low-calorie, low-fat)
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa powder and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve the sauce warm or cool on low-fat ice cream, frozen yogurt or angel food cake.
Top with fresh fruit, i.e. strawberries, raspberries, peaches and apricots.
M-m-m Good, good, good!

title: sugar-free icing
directions: In a saucepan, bring syrup to a rolling boil for 1 minute. Beat egg whites and salt.
Pour hot syrup over stiffly beaten eggs and continue beating until it forms peaks. Add vanilla and a few drops of food coloring (optional).
Makes enough to ice a large layer cake.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine cabbage, green onions and chicken; cover and chill if made ahead.
In a small bowl, stir together sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and flavor packet from noodle soup.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss together.
Cover and chill up to 2 hours.
Toast almonds.
Just before serving, crumble dry noodles from the soup mix into salad.
Add nuts and seeds and toss.
Can add soy sauce or sesame oil for flavor.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off canned fruit into a bowl.
Add juice from cherries and cut them in half.
Add all fruit (canned and fresh) together.
Add the juices to fruit and mix up.
If not sweet enough, can add sugar to desired taste.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: Freeze Oreos and then grind.
Beat milk, cream cheese, Cool Whip and pudding.
Layer Oreo on bottom, pudding mixture, Oreo, mixture, Oreo, etc.
Put in a flowerpot-like dish for added excitement.
Garnish with gummy worms or add silk flowers for "real" dirt cake.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine Milnot, sugar, egg yolks and margarine in pan.
Cover over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans. Spread on cake.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate marshmallow candy
directions: Melt Hershey bars in double boiler.
Put layer of marshmallows in 9 x 9 x 2 pan and pour chocolate over them.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil hamburger in frypan with chopped onion, bouillon and water.
Drain some for gravy.
Make mashed potatoes.
Drain can green beans, carrots or corn.
After hamburger is drained, put in casserole with a little water from hamburger.

title: squash casserole or sweet potato
directions: Cook and mash squash.
Combine and beat sugar, melted margarine, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add this mixture to the squash.

title: ethel's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend in.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: veggies with mushroom sauce
directions: Chop and steam veggies.
Then cook the soup per directions on can.
Pour over veggies as a sauce.
Delicious and fast!

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 the batter on a greased cookie sheet with sides (10 x 15-inch).
Spread pie filling over batter by spoonfuls on top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cam's fruit pancakes
directions: Bring raisins to a boil in water to soften; drain them.
Drain canned fruit.
Combine all fruit in large bowl.
Add yogurt.
Puree in food processor or mash well.
Soften cream cheese in milk.
Add to pancake mix, oil and egg yolks; beat well.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Heat large skillet, lightly greased.
Pour about 1/4 cup mixture for each pancake.
Turn when pancake edges look cooked, cooking both sides until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite pancake syrup and jellies.
Also a mixture of fresh fruit with a dressing of 1 tablespoon honey and Cool Whip.

title: "that's it" caramel frosting
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, sugar and milk.
Heat stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Stir to dissolve sugar; remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat confectioners sugar into mixture until desired spreading consistency is reached.
Add vanilla and mix.
Variation: 3/4 cup chopped nuts.

title: duck and rice casserole
directions: (Riceland seasoned wild long grain rice and Uncle Ben's are good ones to use.)

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pineapple; mix and let set.

title: grandma's sugar pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Put these in the unbaked pie crust, evenly spread.
Mix with finger with 1/2 to 3/4 cup milk in pie crust.
Cut butter into tiny pieces, drop on top of pie.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 450° for one hour, covered with aluminum foil.
Then bake at 350° until done.

title: marshmallow ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until thickened and lemon-colored.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is thick.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme; stir in milk, whipping cream and vanilla.
Freeze in 1-gallon ice cream freezer, following manufacturer's directions.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in mixer, beating 6 minutes at medium speed for 6 minutes.
Bake in greased and sugared 8-inch tube pan. Cool in pan for 10 minutes; turn out and poke holes in top.
Glaze with confectioners sugar mixed with juice of 2 lemons or 1 lemon and 1 teaspoon lemon extract and water.

title: miso soup
directions: *Peel and grate fresh ginger root, then squeeze.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add tomato sauce, taco sauce and taco seasoning to meat.
In a casserole dish, lay 6 tortillas overlapping each other.
Pour half of the meat mixture over them. Spread the cottage cheese that has been mixed with 2 eggs over that.
Put 6 more tortillas on top of cheese/egg mixture.
Pour remaining meat over tortillas and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: easy deluxe bars
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl. Add oleo, sugars, water and vanilla; mix.
Add soda and salt to flour. Sift into the batter; mix. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flavored fruity pebbles cereal treats
directions: Mix in bowl.
Melt 1 (12 ounce) block of vanilla bark over double boiler.
Mix together.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Set in about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add salsa.
Simmer together for 20 minutes.
In an 8 x 8-inch pan, put down a layer of nacho chips. Cover with a layer of meat/salsa mixture. Sprinkle on a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until pan is full, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (20 to 30 minutes).
Serve with sour cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, butter and applesauce; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan.
When done, leave in pan.
Pour icing over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first three ingredients and put in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw 2 loaves frozen bread dough overnight.
Roll out 1 at a time (a little larger than cookie sheet).
Use flour like making bread to roll out.
Pat down on cookie sheet.

title: tuna dip
directions: Break tuna in small pieces.
Add sour cream and dressing mix. Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Good with corn chips, Triscuits or any cracker.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in shortening.
Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add the buttermilk to mixture.
Mix well.

title: easy gooey butter cake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, oleo and egg.
Pour into bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mixture will be stiff.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Mix with mixer the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (30 to 35 minutes).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add margarine and grated cheese.
In separate bowl, beat eggs; add milk and stir.
Pour over macaroni and mix.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into large casserole (sprayed with Pam).
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled beef kabobs
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into 1-inch pieces and place in a zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Combine Italian dressing and wine; pour over steak.
Seal bag and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Cook onions in boiling water to cover 3 minutes; drain well and set aside.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown
sausage	in
a
large skillet. Add the onion and pepper.
Cook
until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add potatoes; cook for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Add eggs; stir. Cook until
eggs
are
set.
Brown
tortillas
in
hot oil.
Divide filling
mixture
between
12 tortillas, placing picante sauce down
the
center.	Sprinkle with cheese (sour cream on side). Burritos can be made in advance, refrigerated or frozen.
Heat in microwave.

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: In large saucepan, add enough salted water to ribs to cover. Cover pan and simmer until almost tender or done, about 1 hour. Meanwhile, in saucepan, melt butter; add garlic and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to boiling.
Drain ribs; place in shallow baking pan.
Pour boiling sauce over ribs. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, basting often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german beef sauerkraut
directions: Trim fat off meat.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Brown meat and onion in oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: honey-orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine orange juice, honey, soy sauce and ginger in cup until blended.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 40 minute, turning chicken twice.
Arrange oranges over chicken.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in a large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is good served warm with ice cream.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until ice cubes are ground into mixture.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Once the mixture has boiled for several minutes place in clean mason jars.
After putting lid and ring on the jars, turn them upside down so that they will seal.
These taste wonderful and are so easy to make!

title: fruit cake
directions: Pour boiling water over fruit, raisins, dates, nuts and soda. Let stand while mixing the other ingredients.
Mix altogether and bake in loaf pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: nut bonbon cookies(a surprise in every bite.)
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together with a fork.
Mix in the flour well with hands.
Chill several hours.
Roll out on a board or table covered with confectioners sugar (approximately 1 cup will be used).
Cut dough in oblong 1 x 3-inch pieces.

title: gorilla banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Then add bananas, flour and baking soda.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a 5 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and carambola salad
directions: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add shrimp and cook 3 minutes or until done.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Peel and chill.

title: nosebag snack mix
directions: Mix all and stir.
Keep in covered container.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Cook the milk and flour until thick; cool.
Beat last 4 ingredients until fluffy, then add cooked mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
(Double ingredients for layer cake.)

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar
and
water in a large pot and boil for 4 minutes.
Let
cool.
Add
rest
of
ingredients
and put into plastic
containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw and mix. Add equal parts of ginger ale.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Roll mixture into small balls.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Place in greased pan 1 loaf raisin bread, diced. Beat together eggs, brown sugar, 1 stick butter and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
After baking, cover with the following sauce.

title: sandi's gooey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add nuts and mix together.
Put into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water; drain and toss with salad oil. Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream; set aside. Brown ground beef; drain and then add salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Mix well.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add dry ingredients, egg, vinegar and water.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Pour in filling and continue baking until crust is brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion or cook chicken; drain. Add all other ingredients; simmer 5 minutes. Dip each tortilla in sauce to coat each side. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and fill with 2 to 3 tablespoons filling. Do all the tortillas; roll as you fill. Cover with all remaining sauce. Top with the shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Make sure all teaspoons are level when measuring.

title: italian tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, spinach, corn, Ricotta and egg.
Place about 1/2 cup mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; arrange seam side down in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and basil; spoon over filled tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt the butterscotch morsels over low heat. Remove and add the peanuts and noodles.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: meat loaf cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put mixture into a cupcake/muffin pan. Fill each hole with the same amount.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix large package of instant vanilla pudding according to the package.
(You can also use 2 small boxes.)
Add to this 1/2 of large Cool Whip and 1/2 of sour cream.
Mix really well.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Keep layering, ending with pudding.
May garnish with bananas.

title: alex's turtle cake
directions: Pour half of the prepared cake mix into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix together sour cream, Tang and milk.
Let set for 20 minutes, then add 1 container Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into Graham Cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Better if chilled.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of margarine (half the stick) in an 8-inch square pan.
Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan.
Place cherries in center of pineapple rings.
Cream together remaining 1/4 cup margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately flour mixture and reserved syrup to bowl, beating just until smooth. Pour evenly over fruit in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: easy cheesy spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic. Add the soups and 1 soup can of water.
Let simmer for 1 hour. Add the cheese, salt, pepper and m.s.g. and stir until the cheese is melted.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain well and add to meat mixture.
Put into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole and top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° until very hot and bubbly.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Cok in three cake pans at 350°.

title: summer dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Serve with assorted chopped vegies.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve cheese in jello and water.
Stir in Pet milk.
Add pineapple and juice and nuts. Place in fridge.

title: rice and broccoli bake
directions: In a saucepan, put broccoli, onion, celery, oleo and 1/2 cup water.
Cook on medium for 5 minutes in a greased casserole dish. Dump broccoli mixture, plus remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Add bread crumbs last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: madison cakes
directions: Boil potatoes well in 1
cups boiling water, until tender.
Strain and save 1
cup
of
the
potato
water.
Mash potatoes into a bowl, add butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt. When potato water and potato
mixture
are cooled to lukewarm, mix dissolved yeast cake in potato water and then combine with mashed potato mixture.
Beat
well.
Sift
in
flour,
beating continuously.
Knead until smooth and spongy, then return to a well-greased bowl.
Cover with a damp tea towel and place away from draft.
Let double in
bulk
for about 3 hours, depending on heat and humidity.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and sweet milk and boil 1 minute, then add peanut butter, chopped nuts, oats and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by spoonful to wax paper and allow to cool.

title: frosty pink punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice cocktail and pineapple juice in a very large pitcher.
Cover and put in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Add the ginger ale.
Pour into glasses and top each with a small scoop of sherbet.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Combine egg, water, 2 tablespoons taco sauce, peppers, salt and pepper.
Coat nonstick skillet with Pam.
Cook egg mixture in skillet, stirring frequently.
Warm tortillas.
Top each tortilla with 1 tablespoon taco sauce and cheese along with eggs.
Place seam-side down on platter.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese. Serves 6.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
In small bowl beat eggs slightly; beat in milk and vanilla until well mixed.
Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries; spoon batter evenly into Bundt pan.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Wrap all ingredients in heavy foil.
Place on a shallow pan or a cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Delicious, quick and easy clean-up.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in eggs, melted butter and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 415° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.
Bake in chilled pie shell.
Do not open door while baking.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: These are approximate measurements.
Extra mayonnaise or mustard may be added according to taste.
Sauce should taste salty.

title: oriental pork patties
directions: Combine pork, bread crumbs, egg, soy sauce, ginger and mustard. Mix well.
Shape into 4 to 6 patties.
Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Brown patties in oil; drain fat.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple with juice.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend together sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water.
Add to frying pan. Stir until thickened and clear.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: raspberry mint cooler
directions: Run mint leaves around inside of punch bowl then drop the bruised leaves in bottom of bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in punch bowl and mix well.

title: cinnamon surprise muffins
directions: Stir 2 Milky Way bars, sliced and 1/4 cup milk in large saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in butter until just melted.
Stir in remaining milk and egg.
Add the flour blended with the soda, cinnamon and salt, stirring only until ingredients are moistened.
Spoon half the batter into 12 cupcake paper-lined muffin tins.

title: curried ham
directions: Note:
You may use chopped chicken or shrimp instead of ham.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape in small balls.
Blend soup and water; heat until mixture begins to simmer. Add meat balls.
Cook until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grape juice float
directions: Combine grape, lemon juice and cider to suit taste.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Fill glasses about 3/4 full and drop a scoop of sherbet on top.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Melt stick of butter and saut onion and bell pepper.
Add Rotel diced tomatoes, and Velveeta.
Cook mixture over low heat, until all cheese melts.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13 casserole dish, over with cheese mixture and bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cook in long casserole dish with pork chops on top for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with tinfoil.

title: wiener wrap
directions: Roll biscuits out.
Wrap around wieners and put in greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300° or until done.

title: fruit dip(or dressing)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender until desired smoothness.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 equal parts.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Roll each biscuit piece in mixture.
Then layer each piece in a Bundt pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Combine shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamed.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla; mix. Beat until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add at low speed of electric mixer.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cooling rack.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl on low, combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pat out 1/2-inch thick on a buttered baking sheet.
Put into freezer until you can cut them. Cut in 1 x 2-inch strips.
Dip in a mixture of melted paraffin and chocolate chips while chocolate mixture is warm.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Pour sauce over it and cook about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk.
Add butter.
Bring to
a boil.
Add
marshmallows
and vanilla.
Reduce heat and cook until melted
or until soft ball stage.
Beat with mixer until thick enough to spread over "Basic Pound Cake Layers".

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, sugar, cooking oil and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mixture will be thick.

title: layered chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, celery, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper and paprika; set aside.
In a greased casserole cover bottom with 1/2 pound diced chicken.
Spread half of soup mixture over the eggs.
Top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and repeat layers twice more using remaining eggs, chicken, soup mixture and cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with butter and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peg's chicken
directions: Grease a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with chipped beef, cut into small pieces.
Roll up chicken breasts in one slice of bacon each and place on beef.
Mix can of mushroom soup with a cup of sour cream and mushrooms.
Pour over top of chicken pieces.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour into 2-quart baking dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and place on bottom of a greased casserole dish. Grate cheese and sprinkle on bread.
Cook sausage and drain. Place between paper towels to rid excess grease.
Then sprinkle over the cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and cayenne pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (uncovered).
Goes well with Curried Fruit.

title: chicken broccoli ring
directions: Arrange crescent rolls with bases overlapping in a star shaped pattern on a big baking stone or cookie sheet, leaving a 3 inch circle in the center.
Mix remaining ingredients in a 2 quart bowl.

title: chicken bundles
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, milk, dill, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and onions.
Unroll crescent dough, separate into 12 rectangles, place on baking sheet and press perforations together.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Mix.
Add thinly sliced apples.
Drop batter by spoon into hot fat.
Serves 12.

title: chili stuffed steak
directions: Cut a pocket in steak by making a horizontal cut through the center of the steak parallel to the surface of the meat, about 1-inch from each side.
Combine cheese, garlic and chili powder. Stuff mixture evenly into pocket of steak.
Close with picks. Place on grid over medium-low coals.
Cover grill.
Cook 30 to 36 minutes for rare to medium.
Cool to slice crosswise.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and baste chicken or beef in oven or on grill.

title: butterflake rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
In large bowl, mix sugar, oil, water and salt.
Stir beaten eggs into yeast mixture and add to water mixture.
Add flour.
Stir well.
Put in fridge overnight or all day.
Roll out adding flour as needed.
Cut rolls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust with flour a 9 x 1-inch pan.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Add brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Fold in flour and nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 40 minutes.

title: easy cocoa
directions: Mix together and store in jars.
Put 1/3 cup in mug and add hot water.

title: carrot cake
directions: Chop carrots.
In mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add Crisco, eggs and carrots.
Mix until moistened.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken broth and 2 cans water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Add biscuits, halved or quartered, to broth. Drop biscuits slowly. Reduce heat slightly.
Add black pepper to taste preference.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl place beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, 2 tablespoons water, Worcestershire sauce and black pepper.
Mix with hands until well combined.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion and saute.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook macaroni in salted water for 5 to 6 minutes; drain. Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: awesome blossom
directions: Cut onion crossways (both ways) about 3/4 of the way through. Soak in ice water about an hour; drain.
Make thin batter.
Dip onion in batter and cook in deep fryer until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Serve with your favorite dip.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit very well.
Then mix it with the other ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Serve in large bowl with or without salad greens.

title: original girl scout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar along with eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill dough about one hour.
Roll very thin and use a tin can (perhaps a soup can) to cut out cookie shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 8-10 minutes. Sprinkle baked cookie with a little sugar.	Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, egg and water.
Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats, butterscotch chips and orange extract.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch dish, layer in order:
lettuce, onion, green pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layers and sprinkle with sugar.
Lay cheese and bacon on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not stir!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into two greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: edna's crawfish etouffee
directions: Combine butter, onion, pepper and garlic in a 2-quart dish. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes covered.
Add paprika, Worcestershire sauce, seasoning and crawfish tails.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to other.
Microwave 10 to 11 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix together sugar, molasses, butter, cinnamon and salt and rub well, then add soda dissolved in water, and the milk, stirring all together.
Add the flour and baking powder sifted together and mix well until smooth.
Add the walnut meats.
Fill buttered and flour dusted pans and bake in 350° oven.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Add juice.
Blend in milk.
Add wafer crumbs and all other ingredients.
Make into 6 rolls.
Butter hands.
Roll cake rolls in coconut or chopped nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Crisco over boiling water.
Stir until chips melt.
Pour 1/2 of chocolate into an 8-inch square foil lined pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 15 minutes. Combine caramels, margarine, water and vanilla; heat over boiling water, stirring until caramels melt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into chocolate lined pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate for about 20 minutes.
Reheat remaining chocolate; spread evenly over caramel. Return to refrigerator and chill for about 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan real good.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large mixing bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time. Press mixture evenly in pan with a piece of wax paper.
Let stand until firm, at least one hour.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares. Makes about 48 squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli. Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
Add onion to taste.
Combine last three ingredients and chill. Toss dressing over broccoli, bacon and cheese just before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients.
Add potatoes and celery.
Chill for 4 hours; sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: best oatmeal cookies(7 to 8 dozen)
directions: Combine raisins and water in small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add baking powder; stir well.
Let cool.
Drain; reserve liquid.
In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, salt and spices.
Add flour mixture and raisin liquid alternately to mixture in bowl, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and quick oats, mixing well. Remove from mixer.
Using large spoon, mix in raisins, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not flatten.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown; cookies should not change color too much in baking and should be soft.

title: peach clafouti
directions: Sprinkle a well buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow oval baking dish with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Distribute peaches over the sugar.
In a blender blend milk, cream, eggs, flour and a pinch of salt.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend the mixture for a few seconds and pour it over the peaches.
Bake the Clafouti in a preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until it is well puffed and golden brown.
Sprinkle the Clafouti with sifted confectioners sugar or vanilla sugar.
Serve it barely warm.

title: tiny tim fruitcake cookies
directions: I usually use more of fruit and less of others.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
To hot macaroni, in same saucepan, add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Put artichoke hearts in oblong casserole dish. Squeeze thawed spinach and place over the artichokes. Beat cream cheese and butter together until smooth, gradually adding milk. Spread mixture over spinach. Sprinkle with good ground of pepper. Top with grated cheese. Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated up to 24 hours. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: 2 minute cherry crisp
directions: Pour filling into 8 inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix. Pour butter over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots (do not overcook).
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper in round slices, then mix with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or longer.
Ready to serve.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; melt cheese and Ro-Tel together.
Stir in beef.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana whip
directions: Mix in blender or mash well with fork and stir.
Add sugar. Ready to use or serve on ice.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage in large frying pan and drain.
In a 10 x 13 baking dish, line croissants and push up around edges.
Add cooked sausage and shredded cheese.
Lightly beat eggs and add salt and pepper and pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour or until eggs are to desired firmness.
Will set as it cools.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: jello surprise
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Set and chill.
Crumble Oreo cookies.
When jello is set, layer part jello, Cool Whip and then cookies, ending with cookies on top.
Kids love it!

title: "bailey's" cream
directions: Blend eggs and liquor. Add all other ingredients and mix until smooth. Serve over ice. Store tightly covered in refrigerator for up to 1 month.

title: crunchy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers, melted margarine and slivered almonds, and place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with slivered almonds and cracker crumbs that have been mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Loosely cover crumbs with foil to prevent them from becoming too brown if needed.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar together.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Form about 1 inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and mash with fork tongs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.
This makes a crumbly peanut butter cookie.

title: old fashioned chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Place the first 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat 3 or 4 minutes. Stir in nuts and peanut butter. Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake for 30 minutes. Cool in pan. Cut in squares or wedges. Makes 12.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in a Bundt pan or deep round pan with a solid bottom.
Place pan in a 350° oven to melt the butter.
Set pan aside when melted.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Roll 1 ounce ham or beef in each chicken breast and "pin" with a toothpick.
Mix soup and sour cream in a mixer until blended. Place breasts in baking pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: alberta mccloud's cream sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; add water and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar slowly and beat well.

Add lemon extract. Slowly add sifted flour, cornstarch and baking powder and beat. Then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in a very slow oven (may be 300° to 325°). If top begins to brown too much, put a piece of brown wrapping paper over it.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and core apples, slice into greased pan and pour lemon juice over top.
Blend flour, salt, sugar, spices and shortening as for pie crust.
Spread over apples and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a small bowl, mix tomato sauce, Karo light corn syrup and mustard.
Now, in a large bowl, mix 3/4 cup of the tomato mixture, 2 slightly beaten eggs, finely chopped, peeled apple, bread crumbs, onion, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Add ground beef; toss to blend.
Put in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish and form a loaf.
Cover with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Spread in 9-inch pie pan. Layer on top lettuce, onion, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: smoked sausage chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp.
Remove.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Pour off drippings.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, sausage and bacon; stir and heat slowly 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve.

title: doris' jalapeno pepper poppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove seeds. Stuff with 2 tablespoons of cream cheese. Wrap with slice of bacon and secure with toothpick. Place on broiler rack that has been coated with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: turtle cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour half in the pan. Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sanders frosting
directions: Cook the flour and milk to custard and cool. Mix the margarine, Crisco, sugar and vanilla. Add to cooled mixture and beat 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter parfaits
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, milk, corn syrup and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; beat smooth with rotary beater.
Cool.

title: quesadillas
directions: Place six tortillas on flat surface.
Spread about 1/2 teaspoon of Tabasco brand green pepper sauce on each.

title: pineapple granny cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Before baking, sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven. Pour topping over hot cake.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread loaf; remove center leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite-size pieces.
Cover shell with top.
Place on cookie sheet with bread pieces.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.
In large skillet, saute celery, red pepper and onion in margarine.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Spoon mixture into bread loaf. Serve hot with toasted bread pieces and vegetable dippers.

title: unbeatable cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Leave 4 inches between cookies.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Contains no fat, no cholesterol.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in oil in a large skillet on medium heat until soft.
Push to one side of skillet.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring well, to crumble beef.
Drain, if necessary.
Add tomatoes and break into smaller pieces.
Add tomato paste, basil, oregano and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: peach crisp delight
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in sifter and sift into bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Peel and slice peaches and arrange in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches and bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Excellent with Blue Bell Homemade Vanilla Ice Cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Dissolve baking soda in water and add to mixture; mix well.
Stir in flour. Roll into balls, flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Cut clean, unpeeled potatoes into even wedges.
Boil for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Spread in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake again for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown and cheeses are melted.
Serves 4.

title: old-fashioned apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar until well blended.
Cook ina heavy pan over low heat until dark and of spreading consistency, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. More or less space may be used to suit individual taste.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine chopped green pepper, vinegar, sugar and Tabasco in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pectin and food coloring.
Return pan to medium heat; bring mixture to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes and pour immediately into hot, sterilized pint size jars.
Seal with paraffin.
Yield:
7 cups.
Jelly may be stored in a cool dry place for up to 12 months.
Serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: potato and chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and chicken.
Mix salt, pepper, flour, melted butter, milk and soup.
Pour over chicken and potatoes.
Top with bread crumbs or potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven, covered, then remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain peaches, pears, apricots, cherries and pineapple chunks. Sprinkle bananas with lemon juice.
Mix all fruits together with the bananas.
Transfer to a 3-quart glass baking dish.

title: potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with water and bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about 15 to 30 minutes. Drain and cool. Place in bowl. Add eggs, salt, pepper, onion and sweet pickle. I usually sprinkle Mrs. Dash over this. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over potato mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, cranberry sauce, celery and pecans.
Put into a 12 x 8 2 inch pan or your favorite mold, sprayed lightly with cooking spray.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold and serve on lettuce.

title: hamburger gravy over potatoes
directions: Over medium heat, combine the ground beef, milk and margarine in a large saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over hot potatoes.

title: seelbach's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; add granulated and brown sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Stir to blend.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Stir into meat flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Cook, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add egg; stir.
Continue cooking on medum-high until thick.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Roll 1 package crescent roll dough into a rectangle on flour board.
Line pie plate or rectangular 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spoon in meat mixture; cover with layer of Monterey Jack cheese slices.
Roll out second package crescent rolls for top.
Cover pan with dough; cut slits into top. Brush with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If top browns too fast, cover with foil last 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: magic lemon pie
directions: Cream egg and sugar.
Add juice and bring to a good boil. Pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Whip cold milk stiff.
Fold in jello mixture, then pour into pie plate greased and lined with vanilla wafers.
Put in refrigerator for 12 hours. Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat nuts, sugar and butter in heavy iron skillet over medium heat.
Stir constantly until nuts are toasted and sugar is golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Stir in vanilla.
Spread mixture on sheet of aluminum foil.
Cool and break into clusters.

title: kahlua
directions: Blend sugar and boiling water until dissolved. Remove from heat and add coffee.
Cool and add vodka.
Pour into 1/2 gallon bottle.
Add vanilla bean (break up). Age at least 3 weeks with tight closure.
Shake bottle occasionally to preserve setting.

title: egg and artichoke casserole
directions: Finely mince onions using half of the tops also.
Cut the artichokes in thirds and reserve oil.
Saute onions and garlic in artichoke oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 as main dish. Can be tripled and serves 30 for brunch, cut into 2-inch squares. Can be prepared a day ahead and refrigerated.
Re-warm about 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese jam spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a round jello mold. Allow to chill for several hours.
Unmold by setting in hot water. Fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix in sugar and flour. Pour mixture over pineapple chunks placed in bottom of glass casserole dish. Top with cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients; set aside. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Alternate additions of pumpkin and dry ingredients. Stir in nuts and cranberries.
Pour batter into 2 lightly greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until bread tests done.
If desired, drizzle with icing (mix just enough cream or milk into confectioner sugar to make a slightly running consistency).
Garnish with walnut halves and cranberries.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain. Add pepper, onion and mushrooms. Saute until onion is clear.
Pour everything including rice and consomme in a large casserole dish, uncovered, and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: lemon-strawberry merry
directions: In punch bowl, combine lemonade, orange juice, strawberries and water.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Add chilled ginger ale and ice or ice ring just before serving.
Mix well.
Makes 2 1/2-quarts, 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; add cream cheese and mix well.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Stir in garlic, pepper and onion.
Add hot pepper.
Serve with salsa and corn chips.

title: chef salad in a roll
directions: Hollow out centers of both halves of rolls.
Spread each half with butter or margarine.
Line bottom halves of rolls with lettuce or chicory leaves.
Drizzle with 1/2 of the salad dressing.
Top with layers of chicken, tomato, ham or bologna, cheese, and egg slices.
Cover with more lettuce or chicory leaves, drizzle with remaining salad dressing and garnish with strips of pimiento.
Cover with top halves of rolls.
Wrap and pack for lunch.

title: rumaki
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer: Mix 1 stick of butter with graham cracker crumbs; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off excess fat.
Stir in onion, soup, ketchup and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve between split hamburger buns.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until well done.
Cool.
Add next 3 ingredients (mixed).
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine and sprinkle on top of chicken and sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put lentils in water and bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place flour in a bowl along with a pinch of salt and baking powder.
Blend with a fork.
Make a well in the center and add egg yolk.
Blend in egg yolk and gradually add the chicken stock. Combine and knead until a workable mass comes together, adding additional
flour or stock if needed.
Let the dough rest for about 10 minutes.
Roll dough out on a well-floured surface.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and celery in olive oil in large heavy pot.
During last minute of sauteing, add the minced garlic.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, spices and cheese; simmer 1 hour, covered.
Brown ground beef and add to tomato sauce.
Simmer another 1/2 hour.
Ten minutes before you serve the sauce, add the 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of baking soda.
This will cut the acid.
I usually put baking soda in when I put the spaghetti in water to cook.
Makes about 2 quarts sauce.

title: favorite apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set the pineapple aside. Place juice in a saucepan; add margarine, sugar and lemon juice. Bring to a boil. Combine the cornstarch and cold water until smooth; add to the saucepan, stirring constantly.
Return to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Chill.
Stir in mayonnaise. In a large bowl, combine pineapple, apples, grapes, poppy seeds and cooked dressing.
Fold in pecans just before serving.
Yield: 14 servings.

title: 3 layer pudding
directions: Add milk to pudding.
Beat until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: corby's cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients together for crust.
Place on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl and pour on top of crust.
Bake for 45 minutes and leave in oven (with door open) for 1 hour.
Top with cherries, blueberries, etc.
Enjoy!

title: mock margaritas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 4-quart plastic container. Mix well.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to use.
Spoon 2 cups of the frozen mixture into blender; add 1 cup club soda.
Blend to desired consistency.

title: deviled meatball appetizers
directions: Combine egg and 1/4 cup beer.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, salt and thyme.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 40 meatballs (1-inch).
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice and chili powder according to taste.
Simmer one hour.
Add kidney beans and noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all together and top with crumbs (sprinkle).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche in hash brown potato crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 to 10-inch glass pie plate with nonstick spray.
Drain shredded potatoes on paper towels and squeeze out excess moisture.
Place in medium bowl and mix with onion and Egg Beaters.
Mix flour and seasoned salt together; then mix into potato mixture until evenly distributed.
Pat this mixture in pie plate so it is evenly spread over bottom and sides to the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate if not using immediately.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter; mix in sugar thoroughly.
Add peanut butter.
Mix by hand.
Form into balls about half size of walnuts.
Insert toothpick and place on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Place in freezer until firm.
Dip about 3/4 of ball in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in freezer or refrigerator.
Use same dipping chocolate as for Chocolate Covered Cherries.

title: french onion soup(french)
directions: Boil water. Turn down to medium. Add onions, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for approximately 1 hour. Add salt, pepper and brown sugar to taste.
Simmer for an additional 1 hour.
Place in bowls with croutons.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Serves 6 to 8.
Oven temperature:
Medium.
Cooking time:
2 hours.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Layer bottom of pie pan or 11 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan with jalapenos.
Top with 2 cups shredded cheese.
Beat 6 eggs with approximately 1/8 to 1/4 cup milk.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan and simmer for 20 - 30 minutes. If simmering longer use 4 quarts of cider.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in pan; dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk and roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in pan, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes; turn and bake 15 minutes.
Mix soup and 1 cup buttermilk and pour around pieces. Bake until tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons for each mug of tea.
Add hot water and stir.
Keep in airtight container.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to a hard boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and pour into a greased rectangular cake pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: barbecue rice and beans
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper and garlic.
Drain off the fat. Add in beans, water, sauce, bouillon and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in the rice; remove from heat and cover.
Let stand at least 5 minutes, then stir again.
It's ready when all liquid is absorbed.

title: microwave minestrone
directions: In 3-quart casserole, cook onion and garlic on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until tender.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, kidney beans, carrots, macaroni, oregano and water.
Cook, covered, on High until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 18 minutes.
Stir once. Add spinach.
Let stand, covered, until macaroni is tender, about 5 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 main dish servings with about 230 calories per serving.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out; immediately press chocolate kiss in center of each cookie; remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles in 1-quart water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 5 minutes.
Brown beef and onion together; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, soup and noodles and beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with olives.
Top with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la king(makes 4 servings)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour.
Cut up chicken and cook. Add all ingredients into saucepan.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fudge pie
directions: In Pyrex pie plate, melt one stick oleo.
Add sugar, cocoa and flour.
Mix and add eggs, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Wipe edges of plate.
Bake at 350° until done (test at 25 minutes).
One half cup nuts may be added to batter.
Bake and serve in same dish.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and 2 cups sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda, adding alternately with sour cream, beating enough to keep batter smooth.
Spoon 1/2 batter into greased Bundt pan.
Combine nuts, cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Sprinkle 1/2 over batter.
Repeat layer.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: rice and tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add mayonnaise or Miracle Whip to taste.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix
Jell-O,
sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Add cream cheese,
pineapple	and
baby food.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour mixture into a dish, top with chopped nuts and chill.

title: 3 year old helper cake
directions: Wash helper's hands.
Preset oven.
Put cake into bowl.
Get out eggs.
Put spilled cake mix back into bowl.
Get out oil.
Pick up broken eggs from floor.
Measure water.
Remove egg shells from batter.
Tell helper next time not to lift electric mixer from batter when it's still running.
Wipe counter walls, being careful not to slip on floor.
Remind helper a taste is not a cupful.
Get out shortening to grease pan.
Gently remind helper to grease pans first!
Comfort helper who is crying because pan slipped from her hands and spilled onto her shoes.
Suggest to helper that sometimes grownups are better at carrying things without spilling.
Clean up helper.
Put on T.V.
Turn off oven.
Wash dishes, counter walls and floor.
Change clothes.
Call bakery.
Take aspirin and lie down.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased baking dish.
Set dish in water in oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie(can be used with other berries)
directions: Cook first three ingredients until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Let cool, then add 1 1/2 pints strawberries to which you have added sugar to taste.
I crush my berries.
They take the sugar better.
Add berries to the first mixture, then into the pie crust.
Let set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin swirl squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, 1 1/2 cups sugar, oil and 2 eggs, mixing well until well blended.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well. Combine cream cheese and remaining sugar and egg, mixing until well blended.
Spoon pumpkin mixture into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over pumpkin batter.
Cut through batter with a knife several times for marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen squares.

title: vanilla, almond pudding
directions: Mix crust together and put in 9 x 12 pan.
Brown at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Watch carefully. Cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Make into balls.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and wax.
With toothpicks, dip candy balls in chocolate.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meatball supreme
directions: Blend soup and water.
Measure out 1/4 cup of this mixture; combine with beef, egg, salt, bread, onion, parsley and pepper. Shape 12 meatballs; brown meat in shortening.
Add remaining soup. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir now and then.
If sauce is thin, remove cover and cook a few additional minutes.

title: yellow squash and onions
directions: Heat butter in
a
skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until
tender,
but not browned.
Add squash, water, salt and pepper.
Reduce
heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased loaf or Bundt pan.
May use 2 loaf pans per recipe.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: best bean salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: quick chicken bake
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes. Rest 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: berans' biscuit bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan, sprinkling chopped nuts on each layer.
Melt brown sugar and margarine together.
Pour over biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together graham crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Separately mix cake mix with oil, water and eggs. Alternate layers of cake mix and crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Ice with mixture of 2 cups icing sugar, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons butter.

title: sugar snaps and peas(preparation time:  5 minutes.  cooking time:  4 minutes.)
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine oil and onions.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir in peas; cover tightly.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in snap peas; cover.
Microwave on High 1 minute more.
Serves 2.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or angel food cake pan. Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Spread in pan. Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Stir together; refrigerate.
The kids love this one!!

title: 4 layer chocolate cake
directions: Combine and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Chill.

title: sally lumn cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar and cream together.
Add eggs and mix until creamy.
Add salt, baking powder and powdered milk (or add whole milk instead of powdered milk and water).
Add flour, pudding and small amount of vanilla.
Add water and cream together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Delicious with any topping or not any.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Ferst you pnots and you speit, you speit.
Thin jam and you speit.
Pnot boder and jam.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix butter, syrup and sugar and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Stir until foamy and pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour in 200° oven.

title: caramel nut brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
(May melt in microwave if desired.)
In mixing bowl, combine remaining 1/3 cup milk with cake mix and margarine; mix well.
Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips over crust.
Top with caramel mixture, spreading caramel to edges of pan.
Top with spoonfuls of remaining cake mixture; press gently into caramel mixtures. Sprinkle with remaining nuts, pressing lightly into top.
Bake at 350° for an additional 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: souper chicken
directions: Put half of wine in bottom of casserole dish.
Add soup mix and mushrooms.
Lay chicken on top.
Pour remaining wine over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Put over linguini.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate.
Mix gelatin, pudding mix and water in medium saucepan until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook at medium heat until boil.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes.
Stir in fruit.
Spoon over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Garnish.

title: beans and wieners waikiki
directions: Cut pineapple into chunks, reserving 3 or 4 rings for garnish. Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Simmer 5 minutes; add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and brown sugar; heat until bubbly.
Mix pork and beans, pineapple mixture, pineapple chunks and wieners.
Stir gently to blend.
Place halved rings on top of casserole.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 minutes. Serve with chow mein noodles.
Serves 6 generously.

title: orange shake
directions: Combine the ingredients in electric blender. Blend 30 to 45 seconds on liquefy or until ice is broken.
Makes 2 servings.

title: orange glazed pork loin roast
directions: Combine the salt, garlic, thyme, ginger and pepper; rub over entire roast.
Place roast with fat side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 2 hours. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine brown sugar and flour.
Stir in the remaining glaze ingredients until smooth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Brush some of the glaze over roast. Bake 1 hour longer or until a meat thermometer reads 160 degrees, brushing occasionally with glaze.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with remaining glaze.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: estelle's chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (except egg whites). Add small can evaporated milk; mix until creamy. Add can of water, more if needed. Stir slowly over low heat until thickens. Pour into cooked/cooled pie shell. Beat egg whites, 2 tablespoons sugar and pinch of cream of tartar. Spread meringue over pie and bake until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine rice, marshmallows, pineapple, cherries and nuts. Whip cream, gradually adding sugar and vanilla.
Fold into rice mixture.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put the ingredients in layers as they are listed.
Let set 2 hours in refrigerator, then toss before serving.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Then add the rest of the ingredients; stir well.
Bake in muffin tins at 425° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Can keep unused batter in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: orange surprise congealed salad
directions: Stir the Jell-O with the boiling water until dissolved.
Add the orange juice and stir into Jell-O mixture. Add the pineapple and oranges.
Mix well. Refrigerate until firm in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: crab cake supreme
directions: Pick over crab meat to remove any cartilage.
Mix all ingredients.
Let crab mixture sit for 20 or 30 minutes.
Remove mixture and roll into cakes.
Do not over fry.

title: mexican rice(from mexico)
directions: In a food processor or blender puree tomatoes and garlic.
Add to enough hot water to make 4 cups.
Add 2 or 3 cubes.
Set aside. In heavy saucepan, put oil and rice.
Cook until golden brown. Pour off excess oil.
Pour tomato mixture in rice and salt; bring to a boil.
Cut an onion in fourths, reduce hat and place onion on top.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Buen Provecho!

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Soften cream cheese with fork.
Chop remaining ingredients and add to cheese.
Spread on 10 to 12 tortillas and roll up. Refrigerate 2 hours and slice into 1-inch pieces for serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (not bread).
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut off top of bread and tear out insides.
Tear into pieces to dip. Put filling in bread.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into crust.
Freeze at least 1 hour before serving.
Store in freezer.

title: date and chip cake
directions: Put dates into bowl.
Pour boiling water with one teaspoon of soda over dates.
Cream shortening; add one cup of sugar and two eggs.
Cut dates into small pieces (can purchase dates already cut into small pieces).
Mix dates in the water/soda mixture with shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and vanilla. Stir mixture together and place in a greased square pan.
Before baking, add brown sugar and chocolate chips together.
Mix well; sprinkle on the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: swedish sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light; add sugar, 1/3 cup at a time. Continue beating.
Add water, then flour mixed and sifted with baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold egg whites into mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Good with strawberries and cream.

title: black-eyed pea corn bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain and set aside.
Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, soda, baking powder, oil, eggs and buttermilk in bowl; mix well.
Stir in corn, black-eyed peas, jalapeno peppers, sausage and half the cheese.
Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set in center.
Yield: 12 servings.
Approximately per serving, cal 337, prot 11 g, carbo 19 g, fiber 3 g, T fat, 24 g, chol 68 mg, sod 591 mg.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients. Make the dressing of sugar, cheese, salt, pepper and Miracle Whip. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of layered mix. Spread dressing on top. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: fudge candy and icing
directions: Cook sugar, milk and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Cool 1 minute.
Beat on high.
Pour into wax paper-lined pan.
Let set; cut into squares.
If used as icing, after beating, ice cake.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and serve chilled.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On wax paper combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat in hot margarine, cook chicken until brown on both sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water, stirring to loosen brown bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Dip each piece of biscuit into melted butter; roll in brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in pan, stacking biscuits on top of one another.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 300° to 350° oven.

title: eirkuchen(pancakes)
directions: Whip up eggs; add milk.
Sift sugar, salt and flour.
Mix all ingredients and fry.
Put sugar on and roll up.
Serves 4 people.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Put mashed potatoes in a baking dish.
Top with cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in hot oven until cheese is melted and topping is golden brown and bubbling.
This can be prepared in advance and frozen.
Serves 6.

title: ham steak grill
directions: Cut ham into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook bacon until crisp, cut into quarters and set aside.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
In same pan, brown ham on both sides.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Place 1 pineapple ring on each piece of ham.
Add brown sugar to pineapple syrup.
Pour over ham in skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon syrup over ham; top with cheese and bacon pieces.
Cover and cook until the cheese melts.

title: nacho snack treat
directions: Fill a plate 1 layer thick with Tostito chips.
Add picante sauce.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese as desired.
Put in microwave for 30 seconds and enjoy.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Mix all together and shape into balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or microwave for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: brandy puffs
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in the sugar, mandarin peel and shortening.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into the egg mixture alternately with the mandarin juice and brandy to make a smooth batter.

title: frosty green grapes
directions: Mix all together. Cover grapes well.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the pudding and milk together well.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Crumble Oreo cookies.
Line pan or dish with cookies and pour pudding mixture over cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In pan on top of stove, mix Coke, catsup and butter.
Add chicken and simmer until tender and sauce is thick.
Easy and delicious barbecued chicken!

title: blueberry sky pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add lemonade and condensed milk.
Mix well.
Fold in 3/4 of whipped topping and 2/3 of pie filling.
Spread into cracker crust.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped topping and remaining pie filling.
Makes two pies.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill before serving.

title: nestle toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine both sugars, vanilla and melted butter; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Combine sifted flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate morsels and pecans and fold in.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Spread and bake for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onions for 3 minutes. Combine onion, 1/4 c. ketchup, 1 Tbsp. mustard, Mozzarella and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Crumble ground meats over cheese mixture, stir until blended.

title: pork chops with baked beans
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place pork chops on beans.
Combine catsup and remaining ingredients and spread over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes to brown.

title: country liver pate
directions: Wash fruit.
Cut peaches and plums in half and remove pits. Place fruit in an enamel, glass or stainless steel saucepan.
Add the wine, water, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Cook, uncovered, until fruit is soft, about 30 minutes.
Put through a fine sieve to remove seeds.
Return liquid and fruit pulp to saucepan and reheat.

title: choco-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil the water, sugar and food coloring; put sliced ripe strawberries, as many as you like, and put in pie crust.
Take 1 c. water and mix in 3 TBSP. cornstarch, cook until thickened slightly.
Add 1 sm. pkg. of strawberry jello and stir until dissolved, pour over mixture in crust.
Cool overnight.
Before serving put whipped cream or cool whip on top!

title: raisin rock cookies
directions: Cream shortening until light.
Add sugar and blend in unbeaten egg.
Combine milk and molasses and add alternately with dry ingredients to mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Cool, then add oranges and Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, corn syrup, brown sugar and salt.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes; stir and cook an additional 3 1/2 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Pour over popped corn in large brown paper bag.
Roll down top and do not open until done.
Put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake well; put back in microwave for 30 seconds.
Shake well and put back in for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well and put back in for 20 seconds. Put in large bowl or pan and let cool.
As it is cooling, stir so it doesn't stick together.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Drain grease off.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Heat until it boils and pour over large bowl of popped popcorn, approximately 5 to 6-quarts.

title: cabbage jambalaya
directions: Saute meat, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Season with various seasonings.
Add tomatoes, cabbage, rice and water.
Cook in heavy cooker with lid, either on low heat on top of stove or in oven at 325°, until rice is done, about 45 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel, slice and separate onions.
Place onion rings in baking dish.
Melt the margarine; pour over onions.
Mix the flour and cheese; sprinkle over onions.
