Place in preheated oven; cook until onions are tender, uncovered.
Leave onions in oven, turned off. Cover for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Meanwhile, melt margarine and toss stuffing.
Mix lightly.
Mix squash, sour cream, onion, milk and chicken soup in a separate bowl.
Put into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish and layer with stuffing mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed pepper
directions: Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Boil in salted water for five minutes and drain.
Cook beef, onions and garlic in melted butter, stirring, until it crumbles.
Simmer for ten minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cake:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Mix cake mix, water, eggs, margarine and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Pour into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press potatoes between paper towels to remove moisture.
Press into 8 x 10-inch pan or 9-inch pie pan for crust.
Drizzle butter over.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce heat to 350°.
Toss ham and cheese together and put in crust. Beat half and half with eggs and seasoned salt and pour on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: flounder with crabmeat stuffing
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic salt in oleo.
Add crabmeat, crackers and egg.
Make lengthwise split in one side of flounder.
Stuff with crabmeat mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: v-8 soup
directions: Cook hamburger and onions until they change color; drain. Cook vegetables until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add V-8 juice.
Bring back to boiling.
Put in crock-pot to simmer on medium for 1 to 2 hours.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into baking dish, then bean dip, then chili.
Spread Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake on 350° until cheese bubbles.
Dip chips.

title: "grilled seafood" bart's favorite from the ukrops seafood cookbook
directions: Prepare grill, charcoal or gas, for cooking.
Brush cooking area with vegetable oil.
Combine butter, lemon juice, cayenne pepper and cracked pepper; set aside.
Place steaks on grill; brush with butter mixture.
Grill over a medium-hot to hot fire for 5 minutes.
Turn and brush with butter; cook additional 5 minutes.
Top with lemon and parsley.

title: canned pear butter
directions: You will also need 1 (8-ounce) canning jar.

title: virgina's delight
directions: Mix apple pie mix, raisins and pineapple, using juice also. Add well drained carrots.
Mix sugar, flour and salt and add. Pour in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar, milk and soda in a large saucepan and cook to soft ball (230°) stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm enough to remove from paper.

title: spareribs
directions: Combine honey, soy sauce, curry powder and minced garlic.
Put spareribs in baking pan and cook in a 375° oven for 1 hour, basting frequently with sauce.
(Spareribs may be marinated in sauce, if you wish.)

title: "hand me down" cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix and let stand one hour.
Bring to boil and can.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bring crumbs up the rim.
Chill 1 hour before filling.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Mix eggs, cold water and sugar in large bowl. In small bowl, mix Crisco, margarine and boiling water.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: brandy slush(wonderful for holidays or parties!)
directions: Boil and cool 7 cups water and sugar in large pot.
In another pot, put 2 cups water.
Add tea bags.
Boil and cool.
When both pots are cool, mix together and add orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Freeze overnight.
Fill 1/2 glass with slush and 1/2 with ginger ale.
Garnish with a cherry.
Wonderful!

title: cocktail cheese quiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, blending just until mixed.
Spray miniature muffin tins liberally with nonstick spray.
Fill each cup 7/8 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes and cool in pans 5 minutes before removing.

title: meat loaf cooked in crock-pot
directions: On medium heat, mix ground beef, salt, crackers, grated onion, 1 egg and tomato juice or milk.
Mix well.
When half done, take the mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.

title: sex in a bowl
directions: Blend cake mix, 1 package of instant chocolate pudding, oil, water, vanilla, eggs, sour cream and 6 ounces of chocolate bits. Bake at 325° in a 10 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with spoon handle.
Pour Kahlua over.
Cut into brownie-size pieces.
Get large punch bowl.
Layer this dessert: chocolate cake pieces, chocolate pudding, La Creme, candy bars and chocolate bits.
Keep repeating, finishing with La Creme and chocolate bits.
This makes a very large but excellent dessert.

title: apricot-orange congealed salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and jello (dry) until blended. Add baby food and pineapple; blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into square pan.
Top with nuts and/or coconut.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pour over carrots and chill.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut each slice into 4 pieces. Alternate layers of bread and cheese in casserole.
Mix eggs with milk and seasonings; pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well; make little balls out of mixture.
Put in candy paper cups; pat down with a spoon.
Melt the chocolate chips; spoon over the tops of balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: barbecue ribs san fernando
directions: Parboiling:
Place 1 side (or slab) of ribs, 1 medium quartered onion, 2 cloves, 1 bay leaf, 1 celery top, 1 teaspoon thyme and 1/4 teaspoon ground pepper in a large pot and barely cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 40 to 45 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: puffy omelet
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add hot water, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cut and fold the whites into the yolks until mixture is well blended.
Butter the sides and bottom of your pan.
Spoon the omelet mixture into the pan evenly.
When well puffed and brown, put the pan in a 375° oven to finish cooking the top.
May sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: chicken wings oriental
directions: In a saucepan, melt all ingredients.
Pour over chicken; marinate.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Mix until blended.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Add egg whites by folding them in.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: turkey-noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles and turkey in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add noodles and turkey.
Cook an additional 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: funny cake
directions: Part I:
Beat ingredients together; divide in two and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: white trash
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in 6-quart or larger container.
Melt next 5 ingredients over low heat.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well, then dump all the mixture into a white garbage bag into which you have put confectioners sugar.
Shake to mix.
Keeps well if stored in airtight container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip together the Cool Whip and milk.
Add fruit, lemon juice and nuts.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: homemade ice cream(for 6 quarts)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into ice cream freezer, adding enough regular milk to raise mixture to one gallon line.
Add any kind of fruit to mixture before freezing as you like.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Gradually stir in milk.
Beat egg whites at high speed with electric mixer until stiff but not dry.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into 8 (10 ounce) custard cups, coated with cooking spray.
Place cups in a large shallow pan.
Add hot water to depth of 1-inch into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until edges are brown.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in one egg at a time. Thoroughly mix.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add alternately with sour cream mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: pizza salad
directions: Pour over Viva Italian dressing (whole bottle).
Marinate overnight.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter or margarine and milk; bring to a boil. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir mixture until melted.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and let set overnight to cool.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Cook on High for 3 minutes; stir.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda. Place popped corn in brown paper grocery bag (large).
Pour mixture over popped corn; shake.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes and shake.
Cook again for another 1 1/2 minutes and shake again. Pour into bowl; let cool.
Break up.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it melts completely.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes, spoon desired size pieces onto wax paper.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips and shortening (Crisco).
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon heaping teaspoons into 1-inch paper candy cups or paper-lined small muffin cups, filling each cup about half full.
Refrigerate until firm.
Peel off paper cup if desired.
Makes 14 to 16 candies.

title: chocolate philly fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours or overnight. Cut into squares.
Garnish with additional nuts, if desired. Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown meat and add spices, beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and onions.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Crush the Fritos. Line baking dish with Fritos.
Add layer of meat and spice mixture and a layer of cheese.
Continue in layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press in a oblong pan.
Brown in oven at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Set aside until thick.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put a thin layer of Cool Whip mixture over crust, then pudding and rest of Cool Whip.
Top with nuts or coconut.

title: spicy meatballs(cocktail size)
directions: Combine ingredients; roll into cocktail size balls and brown until done.

title: cookies "n" cream
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients with spoon.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
Cut in squares.
Serves 15.

title: tuscan tomato soup
directions: Heat the oil and butter in a heavy kettle.
Cook the carrots, celery and onions for about 20 minutes, or until very tender.
Add the tomatoes and continue cooking over moderate heat for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Stir in the parsley and basil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook a minute or so longer, and serve hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4. In saucepan melt butter; add brown sugar and cinnamon. Place half of the biscuits in a greased bundt pan. Add 1/2 c. of pecans or raisins. Pour half of liquid over biscuits. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Bake 35-40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Fry chicken in olive oil and butter for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, basil, salt and black pepper; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add wine; simmer for 10 minutes.
Put noodles into casserole.
Serve chicken and sauce over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp medley
directions: Saute shrimp in garlic and butter on high heat just enough to brown on both sides.
Take from skillet and saute red pepper and onion until translucent.
Pour in tomatoes and sliced squash and zucchini and cook vegetables until crisp.
Add shrimp long enough to heat, then add chili powder.
Cook rice as directed.
Serve over rice or rice as side dish.
Really good!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet & sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan combine Brown Sugar and Cornstarch.
Stir in Red Vinegar, Chicken Broth, Green Pepper, Pimento, Soy Sauce, Garlic Powder and ground Ginger.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Makes 1-1/4 cups of sauce.

title: layer cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar together. Add flour, baking powder, soda, eggs and buttermilk, mixing well. Stir in vanilla. Bake in three 8-inch layers at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost with Caramel or Chocolate Icing.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat at medium speed until well blended and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in the flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on a rack.

title: great grandma's soft molasses cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar with shortening and molasses until well blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with boiling water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes or until center springs back.

title: carameled sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and arrange in greased baking dish.
Mix salt and sugar with flour.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter and pour milk over casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood bisque(makes 5 servings)
directions: Saute onions in the butter until tender.
Add flour, cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, forming a good roux.
Gradually add the half and half and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a small bowl beat eggs about 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Pour eggs into a larger bowl; gradually beat in granulated sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan, spreading batter to corners.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Loosen cake and invert onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Remove foil and trim off edges.
Roll up.
Cool.
Then unroll, remove towel and spread whipped topping.
Roll up.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Fry hamburger or sausage, pepper, onion and celery until tender.
In a large bowl, mix soups, rice and water well with electric mixer.
When soup mixture is mixed well, add meat.
Mix all this together.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Stir often, because rice settles to the bottom.
The last 1/2 hour, add the dry Chinese noodles; leave uncovered.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Mix dates, baking soda and boiling water and let stand in a separate bowl.
Mix granulated sugar, shortening, egg yolk and vanilla.
Combine this mixture with flour and English walnuts.
Put walnuts in flour and fold in date mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease loaf pan and place wax paper in bottom.
Bake 1 hour or until test done at 375°.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and almond.
Beat well.
Add baking powder to flour.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to creamed butter mixture.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, one at a time.
Stir well with spatula until all ingredients are showing well.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Boil and cool first three ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together with cooled mixture.

title: orange-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and add juice.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon. Remove from stove; add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Stir in whipped milk. Pour into pie shells.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: chicken yummy
directions: Place chicken in deep casserole dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and stir slightly.
Continue to bake for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in egg yolks.
Mix in flour, soda, sour cream and flavorings.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until a peak forms.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a well-greased angel food pan.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix vegetables.
Add salt and soak 1 hour; drain well.
Add turmeric, dry mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Cook 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium, stir occasionally.
Put in sterile glass jars and seal.
Yields 10 pints.

title: chicken wings mediterranean
directions: Cut tips from chicken wings and discard; coat wings with mixture of flour and salt. Brown in fat in a large frypan; drain excess fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling. Cover. Cook slowly 30 minutes. Uncover; cook several minutes longer or until sauce thickens. Serve with cooked spaghetti. Makes 4 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put 1 small onion, 1 dill head and stalk plus 1/4 teaspoon alum in jars.
Pack the cucumbers into jars (should be washed cucumbers).
Mix water, vinegar and pickling salt.
Place mixture on stove and stir until it boils.
Pour over cucumbers and pressure until 5 pounds pressure is reached.
Remove from heat.
Let cure 5 weeks before opening jars.

title: play dough(non-edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a Teflon pan.
Cook and stir over low heat until it forms a ball and mixture is not sticky.
Remove from pan and cool completely before storing in airtight containers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix ingredients except potatoes, 1/2 can soup and cheese.
Pat into a large pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with 4 cups mashed potatoes.
Spread rest of soup on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: northern comfort
directions: Chill beater and bowl containing all ingredients except grahams. Whip. Line a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan with strips of waxed paper. Coat bottom and sides of pan with a 1/2-inch layer of the cream mixture. Alternate layers of grahams and the cream, ending with the cream.
Freeze.
Can be double-wrapped and frozen for up to a month. Before serving, refrigerate the night before after turning out onto a serving dish and peeling off the paper.
Slice into 1-inch slices to serve.

title: crabmeat mousse
directions: Heat everything together until cream cheese is melted.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Pour bouillon in crock-pot; cover, set on high.
Cook onions slowly in large skillet in butter; cover and let cook about 15 minutes.
Uncover and add salt and flour.
Stir well.
Add to bouillon in crock-pot.
Add vermouth.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (High for 3 hours).
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top.

title: grandma's quick gingerbread
directions: Sift
together flour, salt, sugar, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and cloves.
Add egg, molasses, melted shortening and
milk.
Stir
in
hot water and mix thoroughly. Pour into
greased	and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry angel food cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 1/2 tsp salt in a sauce pan, slowly add milk. Mix well. Stir often medium heat until mixture is thick and bubbly. Stir 2 Tbsp of the hot mixture into the egg yolks. Return all to hot mixture bring just to boiling. Stirring constantly, remove from heat and add vanilla. Cool. Slice cake in 3 layers. Fold
whip cream
into pudding and fill between layers. Top with raspberries just before serving.

title: martha's sausage dip
directions: Cube Velveeta.
Melt in crock-pot or double boiler.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: lobster cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together, adding eggs and beating well. Then alternately add rest of ingredients.
Makes 4 or 5 layers. Cook in greased cake pans at 325° until lightly brown.

title: fireside mocha
directions: Blend well in blender.
Use
to 3 teaspoons per cup. Fill with boiling water.

title: chile cheese squares
directions: Put half of cheese in greased 9x13 pan put in green chiles, add eggs, then rest of cheese.
Bake at 350 for 35-45 minutes.
Cut into bite size and spear with toothpicks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend until smooth.
For crust, 1 cup Grape-Nuts or granola.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add ground chuck and brown meat, breaking it up as it cooks.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 15 minutes after it reaches the boiling point.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice and sugar water together.
Store in containers in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Pour in ginger ale; serve over ice.
May use mixture less ginger ale for ice cubes.
Serves about 50.

title: betty's chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour alternately with milk. Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan. Place in a COLD oven to start, then set it at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tired wife's supper
directions: Cook macaroni; set aside.
Cook onion, celery and pimento in a little butter until tender.
Add meat, cook until brown; drain. Put macaroni in a casserole dish with tomatoes, add salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture and mix.
Cook at 350° until thick.
Put cheese on top and let it melt.
Serve with Italian bread.
This will get you a big hug.

title: cucumber and green tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, cucumbers, peppers and salt.
Pour salt over the mixture.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Soak 3 hours in cold water.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric and mustard seed. Pour over mixture.
Cook 20 minutes.
Use as many peppers as you like; I put about 6 peppers.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cool rice and mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight. Toss again and garnish with parsley and baby tomatoes.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Mix sugar, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Toss apples in dry mixture to coat.
Put apples into unbaked pie shell and dot with the butter.
Cover with remaining shell, crimping and trimming edges to seal.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes more.

title: shrimp in mustard sauce
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet.
When hot, add shrimp.
Turn and saute very lightly, being careful not to overcook.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon and set aside.
Saute onions in residue in same pan for 2 to 3 minutes.
Deglaze pan with sherry, reducing to 1/2.
Add cream, bring to a boil and reduce heat to thicken.
Swirl in soft butter, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Add shrimp; sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve with hot rice or pasta.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Place in pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except almonds) together and place in casserole. Sprinkle almonds over the top. Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: savory orange roast beef
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Place roast in a large shallow dish. Combine 3/4 cup orange juice and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over roast.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Place roast and marinade in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: luscious squares
directions: Cream butter.
Add 1 cup plain flour.
Sift flour together. Makes a soft dough.
Spread on a heavily greased pan.
Bake in a moderate oven for 10 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add plain flours.
Add baking powder; sift together.
Add nuts.
Pour over first part.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes more.
Leave in pan until cool.
Spread; add butter to powdered sugar.
Add flavoring over cake.
Cut in squares.

title: chris' favorite pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Follow directions on back of double box of pizza.
Add sliced olives, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Cook the hamburger and sausage.
Add green pepper and onion.
Add banana pepper, finely cut.
Add cheese.
Bake until cheese is brown.
Let cool.

title: crock-pot chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot 6 hours on low setting.
Remove and separate chicken from bones.
Return chicken to crock-pot.
Cook noodles according to package.
Put in crock-pot.
Add chicken gravy and stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Do not put chicken skin in pot.
Serves 4.

title: michele's mexican casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook meat until moisture is gone.
Add chopped up onion and cook a minute or so.
Salt to taste.
Add beans, soup and Ro-Tel; heat and stir.

title: cole slaw
directions: Using a food processor, shred cabbage, carrots, pepper and onion.
Remove to a large bowl.
Add celery seed, salt, pepper and enough mayonnaise to coat.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Stir well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: easy bar cookies(graham cracker bars)
directions: Line a cake dish with layer of graham crackers, then mix in a saucepan the following:
butter, coconut, crushed graham crackers, brown sugar and milk.
Boil gently 5 to 8 minutes, stirring often to avoid sticking.
Spread mixture on graham cracker layer, then put another layer of crackers on top.
Frost with white or chocolate icing.
Cut into bars.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in layered pans (greased and floured).

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Bake in a prepared pan (9 x 13-inch approximately) at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golumpka(polish stuffed cabbage)
directions: Break leaves of cabbage off head.
Put about 8 to 10 leaves on dish and microwave on High about 3 minutes or until limp.
Prepare the rest of the cabbage in the same manner.

title: apricot scones with ham and honey mustard
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a cookie sheet; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, 1/8 teaspoon salt and the nutmeg.
With pastry blender, or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in 1 egg and milk just until moistened.
Stir in apricots and raisins.
On floured surface gently knead dough 3 to 5 times until it holds together.
With floured rolling pin roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a floured 2-inch round biscuit cutter, rerolling scraps.
Beat remaining egg with a pinch of salt and lightly brush tops of scones.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool on wire racks.

title: pork chops in gravy
directions: Trim excess fat from pork; set aside.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper; dredge pork chops in flour mixture, reserving remaining flour mixture.
Coat a nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add pork chops and brown on each side.
Remove to a 1-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Add mushrooms, onion and green pepper to skillet.
Saute until tender.
Stir in reserved flour mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour gravy over pork chops.
Cover and bake an additional 10 minutes. Serve over rice.
Yields 2 servings.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add topping.

title: large meat loaf
directions: Mix. Top with tomato sauce or ketchup.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: david's surprise
directions: Chop the onion and add to hamburger meat, then brown meat and add taco seasoning. In a separate pot, add both soups and pinto beans (heat to boil). Then reduce heat and add Ro-Tel for a few minutes. Microwave tortilla shells for a few seconds to soften. Put layer of six shells on bottom of pan. First layer will be the meat, then add the soup to the next layer, followed by the cheese (as much as you want). Repeat until all of the mixtures are gone.

title: superb strawberries
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cream, corn syrup and butter. Boil and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add candy.
Stir to melt.
Cool; serve over strawberries. Store leftovers in fridge.
Also great on raspberries, blackberries, grapes and pineapple.

title: traveling taco
directions: Layer ingredients in pretty appetizer (flat) bowl or pan. Layer in order as listed.

title: chicken 'n dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken pieces until done.
Remove bones.
Mix stuffing with butter.
In baking dish, put 1/2 stuffing, chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread over this mixture, chicken soup, mushroom soup and then celery soup, in that order.
Do not mix.
Pour broth over mixture.
Put remaining stuffing on top.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients (flour, sugar, cocoa, milk, oil and vanilla) and pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle top with 1 cup pecans, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour 2 cups hot water over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes its own hot fudge sauce!

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 425° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce heat to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into pieces.
In skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, pepper, onion and bouillon.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs, flour and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with tomato slices and remaining cheese slices.
Bake 3 minutes longer.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until the mixture leaves the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat and knead until cool.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and heat to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on top and let sit for 10 minutes.

Sift together 4 cups white and 3 cups rye flour. Add to mixture and mix well. Continue to add 4 to 5 cups of white flour until you can knead easily. Knead for 8 to 10 minutes and then allow to rise about 2 hours in a large greased bowl covered with a damp towel.
Punch down and divide into either 4 loaves or 8 pans of rolls.
Let rise, covered with damp cloth.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch pans. Mix and beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Bake about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost with white frosting and spread on coconut.
Then slice a layer of bananas, continuing with next layer the same way.
Do not put bananas on top.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: pavlova
directions: Bev collected this recipe on her trip to New Zealand where it is a favorite dessert.

title: shrimp layered dip
directions: Take a 10 to 12-inch platter or cake plate; spread softened cream cheese evenly over entire platter.
Spoon cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Place shrimp over cocktail sauce starting from outside of platter and lying them flat and spiraling toward the middle of the platter.
Serve crackers on side.

title: yeast rolls(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Dissolve yeast in water in 2 1/2 qt. bowl.
Add sugar, oil, salt, and egg.
Mix to dissolve.
Add 1 c. of flour and mix until smooth.
Cover with cloth.
Place on rack over bowl of hot water. let rise 15 minutes.
Grease pan 12 x 9 inch.
Stir batter, add rest of flour.
Mix good.
Turn on floured board.
Knead 3 minutes.
Divide into 20 pieces.
Shape in balls. Place in pan.
Brush tops with butter.
Cover with cloth.
Place over hot water.
Let rise 25 minutes.
Bake 12 - 15 minutes or until brown.
Brush tops with butter.
(Can be made in mixer.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together and beat first 2 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add and beat well next 3 ingredients.
Sift together last 2 ingredients.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Shape into mound, wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.

title: tuna salad in tomato cups
directions: In bowl, combine tuna, celery, olives, green onions, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in mayonnaise or salad dressing and chopped eggs; cover and chill.
With stem end up, cut each tomato into 6 wedges, cutting to, but not through, base of tomato.
Spread wedges apart slightly; sprinkle lightly with salt. Cover and chill.
To serve, place a chilled tomato on each individual lettuce-lined plate; fill each tomato with about 1/2 cup of tuna mixture.
Garnish with additional sliced pimiento-stuffed olives, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in baking dish; cover with soup.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes.
Uncover and cook about 10 more minutes.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole. Cover with buttered cracker crumbs (additional).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven, until nicely browned.

title: our lefse
directions: Cook potatoes in slightly salted water.
Rice into large bowl and place butter into melt.
If potatoes are too cool to melt butter, place in microwave oven to melt.
Cool overnight.
Next day, add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Form into 2-inch balls. I roll on a canvas covered board with a regular rolling pin covered with a stockinette.
Constantly be working flour into board and rolling pin, so Lefse does not stick.
Transfer to griddle with Lefse paddle.
Bake until light brown spots form on one side.
Flip and continue baking.
Keep baked pieces covered so they do not dry out.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water and butter to a boil.
Add all flour at once; stir until a smooth ball forms. Remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until smooth. Spread into greased 9x13 baking dish.
Bake 400 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and pudding mix until smooth.
Spread over puff; refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Spread with whipped topping; refrigerate until serving. Drizzle with chocolate and caramel toppings and sprinkle with almonds.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook, debone and chop chicken.
Place in 5-quart cooker or crock-pot the chicken, tomatoes, potatoes, onion and okra; cook for 8 hours.
Add corn, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Cook 10 more minutes.
This makes the stew.
If you want soup, add the 3 cups chicken stock.

title: strawberry  jello figs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and let set 1 hour or more. Cook slowly and boil 20 minutes. Add the Sure-Jell and cook 2 minutes longer.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
Tastes and looks like strawberry preserves.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and heat to dissolve jello.
Cook before adding Cokes.
After adding Cokes, let begin to congeal before adding fruit.
Add nuts, then cream cheese last by cubes.
Serve with a mixture of mayonnaise and a little French dressing.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine yellow cake mix, butter and 1 egg; press lightly in pan.
Mix 2 eggs, sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and spoon three rounded teaspoons together per cup.

title: wild rice ham and cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion.
Blend in flour. Gradually add broth until thickened.
Stir in rice and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Add sherry and half and half, carrots, ham, cheese and almonds.
Heat and serve.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and milk together in a large saucepan. As mixture begins to simmer, add egg yolks.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and margarine.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: mint chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap the mints and set aside. In a saucepan, heat margarine or butter, sugar and water.
Add chocolate chips and stir to partially melt.
Remove from heat and continue to stir until melted.
Pour into a bowl and let cool for 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs at high speed.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Chill dough for 1 hour. Line baking sheet with foil.
Roll dough in small balls. Bake for 10 or 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; place mint on each cookie.
Remove cookies to cooling rack as mint softens; spread over cookie to coat.
Yield: 84 cookies.

title: cool cucumber pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. Place in large bowl. Stir in oil, cucumbers and onion. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over salad and toss. Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana dream salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add cold water.
While hot, add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Cover with marshmallows.
Let jello set.

title: party chicken
directions: Spread dried beef.
Place in a casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Wrap chicken breasts with bacon slices.
Lay them on beef.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.
Or, bake for 30 minutes in microwave, turning dish several times.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Blend together soups and flour.
Add sour cream, carrots, onion and salt.
Stir in drained broccoli.
Turn into a 2 quart casserole and combine stuffing and butter.
Sprinkle around on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix the dressing mix with the melted margarine.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Pour squash mixture over top with the other of dressing mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice thin.
Put apples in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Pour water over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour sugar over apples.
Put dry cake mix evenly over apples. Sprinkle chopped nuts over mix.
Slice margarine over top. Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put mixed spices in a bag, grind vegetables.
Let stand in salt water, 1 teaspoon to a quart of vegetables for 1 hour. Drain and add vinegar,
sugar
and bag.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add green color to make green.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Melt chocolate morsels; cool.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
In a small bowl, combine egg whites and salt.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoon 1 inch apart onto brown paper-lined baking sheets.
Bake in a 325° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 50 cookies.

title: hot wings
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow pan.
Melt butter.
Add vinegar and hot sauce to butter.
Stir to mix.
Pour over chicken and marinate 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Ranch dressing on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg and lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Rinse, pat dry chicken.
Dip in egg, then flour.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add additional lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion and drain. Mix together with all remaining ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Other kinds of canned beans can be used. Feeds a crowd!

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half.
Blend food coloring into one half.
On lightly floured board, roll 1 teaspoon plain dough into 4-inch rope.
Repeat with red dough.
Place ropes side by side; press together lightly and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Curve top to form handle of cane.
Repeat until all dough is used.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes or until light brown.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix in order given, adding hot water last.
Bake until cake springs back when touched.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal scotchies cookies
directions: Bake at 375°.
Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon slowly.
Stir in the rest of items.
Drop by cookie sheet (ungreased) by the tablespoon.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: angie's chicken or tuna stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok
or
nonstick skillet.	Add meat, fresh vegetables.
Saute altogether
with
seasonings and serve over rice.
This is low calorie.

title: amazing apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a bundt pan. Cream together oil, sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat just until blended. In separate bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, and nutmeg; mix; add to sugar mixture and stir just until combined. Stir in apples and nuts. Pour into pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 minutes; invert onto a wire rack and cool. Place on a serving plate and pour glaze over cake.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Spread broken pretzels evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour melted butter over pretzels and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat tortillas in oil a few seconds each side.
Put about 2 tablespoons shredded cheese and 1 teaspoon diced onions on each tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. In saucepan, melt margarine, blend in flour; add chicken broth and heat until thickened.
Stir in sour cream and chiles.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: cracker jack
directions: Boil molasses, water, butter, cream and sugar until it hardens in water.
Take off stove and stir in the vinegar, soda and cream of tartar.
Pour over popped corn and spread on board to cool. This amount is sufficient for about fifteen pints of popped corn.

title: christmas dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions and tomatoes in deep bowl with mixer. Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Add garlic salt and black pepper.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: fat-free chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered container at a cool temperature.
Stir well before using.
Makes several batches of cookies.

title: ground beef oriental
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter.
Remove from pan.
Brown beef and rice.
Combine soup, water, soy sauce, pepper, celery and onion.
Stir in bean sprouts.
Lightly bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350° in 2-quart dish.
Serve warm over crunchy Chinese noodles or cooked rice.

title: delicious sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Shape into balls.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion. Drain. Simply dump all other ingredients in pot and cook for 1 hour. Serve with grated cheese, nacho chips and sour cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt cheese; add milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over beans and water chestnuts.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.
Mix in about half of the cake mix, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and the coconut or nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cook box of wild rice in chicken broth.
Mix all together.
Put in casserole.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Bake uncovered until ribs are nice and tender, about 1 hour. Then put barbecue sauce on ribs.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Use a 16 oz. mixing plastic jar with lid.
Peel garlic, set aside.
Mix lemon juice, anchovy paste, Worcestershire sauce and grated parmesan cheese.
Add olive oil, pepper to taste, white wine vinegar and seasoned rice vinegar mix.
Add mayonnaise. Press the garlic into the mixture.
Put lid on and shake.

title: golden carrots
directions: Slice carrots crosswise into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in boiling, salted water 15 minutes; drain.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients, except parsley and almonds, and stir until lumps disappear, cooking over a medium heat.
Add carrots and parsley and toss.
Add almonds just before serving.

title: baked carrots
directions: Scrape and pare carrots and place in casserole.
Cream butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Add water and blend well. Pour over carrots, cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients thoroughly.
Then add dry ingredients until blended.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 35 minutes, in muffin tins.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 3 hours the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer in the following order on a pizza pan: Bean dip, sour cream mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, green onions, Cheddar cheese and top with black olives.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bone and cut into bite sizes.
Save the broth.
Arrange tortillas dipped in chicken broth in a large flat casserole.
Place a layer of chicken on top of tortillas. Sprinkle with garlic salt to taste.
Add peppers, onion (cooked in small amount of oil if desired), soup, chili powder and cheese; pour mixture over tortillas and chicken.
Pour tomatoes with juice over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly through.
This can be prepared and frozen.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add the zucchini and pineapple.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to mixture, blending well.
Stir in nuts.

title: coconut caramel pie(makes two pies.  they can be frozen for months.)
directions: Melt margarine, coconut and pecans in skillet until hot and brown.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer about 1/4 or 1/3 cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Sprinkle about 1/3 of pecans and coconut, then drizzle caramel around over the pies.
Repeat layers until all is used. Freeze.
Takes about 10 to 15 minutes out of freezer until ready to slice.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Spray coat a large 12 x 18-inch baking pan.
Wash chicken and lightly salt each side.
Sprinkle dry rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Arrange chicken (1 layer) over rice, skin side up.
Spread cream of chicken soup over all chicken evenly.
Pour the water over all. Bake 2 hours at 350° until tender.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour and salt into 2-quart bowl. Add onions.
Stir in milk, then egg.
Dough will be soft.
Let mixture set for about 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in vanilla and chocolate until blended.
Gradually beat in flour until blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cookies are soft when hot, but firm and chewy when cool.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: easy ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done; set aside.
Brown the ground beef and onions; drain off excess fat.
In large bowl, mix all of the ingredients together.
Serve about 1/4 cup of cheese for top.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix and press in long baking dish the flour, nuts, sugar, oleo and salt.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix and spread over crust the powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over mixture the lemon pudding and milk.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot bean dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.

title: turkish bulghur pilaf(main dish for 2 to 3)
directions: Stir-fry bulghur in large skillet in butter until it crackles. Meanwhile, boil stock and tomato juice together, then let cool. Add liquid to bulghur.
Cover and simmer over very low flame until liquid is gone (20 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and stir until heated.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies(low-fat)
directions: In bowl, add orange juice, applesauce, honey, milk and vanilla; blend.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to orange juice mixture.
Stir to blend.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Core and peel apples and add to juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook until soft.
Put into crock-pot and add remaining ingredients. Cook on high during the day and low all night.
Keep cooking until no more liquid shows.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: two bean chili
directions: Combine onion and green pepper in 2-quart microwaveable casserole dish, covered.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, including reserved tomato liquid.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 16 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Add to thickened mixture the strawberry Jell-O. Place berries in pie shell.
Pour thickened mixture over berries. Chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: brie in puff pastry
directions: Spread mashed garlic on top of Brie; cover with raspberry preserves.
Wrap Brie in puff pastry and place on Pam-sprayed baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg with water and brush over puff pastry.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately with crackers.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix
well cherries, pineapple, milk and nuts.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Let chill until set.
May be frozen to slice and served later.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Add rice to dish.
Mix water and cream of mushroom soup; pour 1/2 of mixture over rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Measure flour, brown sugar, butter, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt into medium bowl and beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Remove 3/4 cup of mixture for topping and set aside.

title: water whip pie crust
directions: Light
oven;
get
out	bowl, utensils and ingredients. Remove blocks
and
toys from table.
Grease pan.	Crack nuts. Measure 2 cups of flour; wash flour off him.	Remeasure flour. Put flour, baking
powder,
and salt in sifter.
Get dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl which Bobby knocked on floor.
Get another
bowl. Answer
doorbell.

to kitchen.

from bowl.
Wash

Get out eggs. Answer phone.
Take out
greased

Look

Wash table. Wash walls.
Wash dishes.
Call the baker.
