title: moussaka
directions: Saute onions, eggplant
(or zucchini) and tomatoes with salt and pepper in oil
over medium heat; do not brown.
Layer half the eggplant
mixture,
bacon,
and remaining eggplant in deep baking dish.
Combine cheese, milk and egg in bowl.
Beat until smooth. Add
nutmeg
to
taste.
Pour
over
casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hi-c punch
directions: Hi-C and sherbet should be the same flavor.
Keep sherbet frozen until ready to use.
Chill Hi-C and ginger ale.
Pour over sherbet.
Orange is very good.
Makes 18 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time while continuing to beat. Stir in all ingredients except for: 1/2 c. sugar,1/4 c. brown sugar,1/2 tsp. cinnamon and 1/2 c. nuts. Reserve these items for the topping. Pour into a grease 9 x 13 pan. Blend topping ingredients together and sprinkle over batter gently pressing it on. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a
bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake them, a few at a time, in the bag, coating them well with the cheese mixture.
Melt butter on cookie sheet.
Place potatoes in single layer on sheet. Bake at 375° about 1 hour, turning once during baking or until golden brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix
flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
When shortening is mixed well through the flour, combine egg with the yeast and water and mix well.
Add to flour mixture.
Knead together and turn out on floured board, kneading until it forms dough.
Put in
a large bowl, greasing the top and let stand 2 or 3 hours. Then knead
into small rolls.
Let stand an hour.
Grease tops of rolls
with butter and bake in hot oven for 20 minutes.
If you don't
need
to
use
all
the dough at once, store in the refrigerator.

title: corn relish
directions: Add all ingredients in large pan; cook at low heat until done. This recipe varies, depending on how sweet and how hot you need. Just add more or less of sugar, vinegar or bell pepper to suit your taste.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Stir to mix.
Add the eggs.
Beat well.
Add the butter, lemon juice, lemon peel and milk.
Beat well.
Pour the filling into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until the filling is set in the center and the top is golden brown.
Remove from the oven and cool before slicing.

title: enchiladas
directions: I cook these until heated through, at about 350° or 400°, if desired to be browned.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Pare the eggplant, if desired. Cut it into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip each slice into the beaten eggs and then dip them into the bread crumbs.
Saute in the hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Place a layer of eggplant in a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with some of the thyme, salt, Parmesan cheese, oregano and the Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with some of the tomato sauce.
Repeat until all the eggplant is used. Top the last layer with several slices of the Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Follow directions on spice cake mix, except reduce water to 1/2 cup.
Add pumpkin and cinnamon.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: amish baked oatmeal
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients in mixing bowl and spoon into a well-greased 9-inch square dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May want to cover with foil while baking.
Serve warm.

title: b. j. taverns
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes about 6.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Other fruit may be used in the same proportions.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before topping.

title: heartwise coleslaw
directions: Slice cabbage; put into a large bowl.
Add carrots and cucumbers.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, paprika and pepper.
Add to vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts; chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
While still hot, roll in confectioners sugar. Cool on wire rack, roll again in confectioners sugar.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: simple punch
directions: In a gallon jar, mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, sugar and tea. Fill jar rest of way full and stir.
Put in freezer, stirring away from sides as it freezes.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale. This will make it slushy.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, salt and sour cream; mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine. Refrigerate.
When ready to use, put in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Be sure to cover with foil.
This can be made 2 or 3 days in advance.
Good to use when you don't want to have gravy.

title: low calorie vegetarian chili
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients except for beans.
Put 1/3 of mixture into a food processor or blender and process until pureed.
Repeat with rest of mixture, pouring into large pot to simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add beans to pot and simmer 30 more minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool and serve.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate caramel chip pie
directions: Crush cookies; press into an 8-inch pie pan.
Set aside.
Mix yogurt in blender until smooth.
In layers, take turns putting yogurt, chips, topping and syrup into pie crust until all used. Freeze 2 to 4 hours.

title: blueberry pie(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Puree 1 1/4 cups of the blueberries (reserve 1/4 cup for garnish).
Cook pudding according to directions.
Add blueberries and cinnamon.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Let cool, then chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: honey puffs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Makes 24.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: lovers delight
directions: Mix together.
Let stand 24 hours.
Mix now and then.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
In skillet, brown meat, mushrooms and onion in butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add broth, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Gradually blend 1/4 cup water into 2 tablespoons flour and slowly add to sauces.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly blend in sour cream.
Serve on noodles.

title: sweet potato chiffon pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with egg yolks.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake until firm.

title: lemon cups
directions: Add blended sugar, flour and salt to melted butter.
Add lemon juice and rind and mix well.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Stir well.

title: slaw
directions: Mix together and let come to a boil.
Set aside and cool. Pour over 3 pounds chopped cabbage and 2 small onions.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Grind in a food processor or grate together carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apples.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix all until combined.
Spray muffin pan. Fill each muffin cup half full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 min. Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum pot (do not use black iron pot). Season shrimp tails with salt, pepper and paprika, then saute in margarine about 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic to margarine; saute for at least 10 minutes.
Return shrimp to pot and add 2 cups water and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Check for taste. Add more seasoning if necessary.
Add cornstarch and a small amount of water; stir until thick.
Serve over rice; garnish with parsley.

title: diamond fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture melts and is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar, stirring until smooth.
Spoon into a buttered 8-inch square pan; chill until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before cutting into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise and eggs.
Toss lightly with broccoli.
Grease 7 x 13-inch baking dish and add broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle the crumbs mixed with butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes or until cheese bubbles through in 350° oven.

title: rice and tofu casserole
directions: Combine rice and boiling water in covered pan.
Add bulgur. Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Saute ginger and onion.
Add crumbled tofu. Cook several minutes.
Add green peppers, carrots and soy sauce. Cook until pepper and carrots are heated.
Check bulgur and rice. When tender, stir in vegetables.
Microwave, covered, several minutes, then serve.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute chopped green pepper, onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add soup.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Cook noodles.
Drain and combine with chicken mixture.
Pour into 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The crushed cheese crackers are sprinkled on top before baking.
Serves 8.
Freezes well.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Mix spread, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oil in small skillet.
Add garlic and remove skillet from heat.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Brush chicken with oil from skillet, then dip into crumb mixture.
Place on a baking pan and bake at 350° uncovered for about 30 minutes.

title: mushroom-eggplant soup
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add the onions and saute until tender, about 8 minutes.
Add the garlic and mushrooms and saute another few minutes, then stir in the thyme.
Add the eggplant, tomatoes and stock and simmer gently until the eggplant is tender, about 20 minutes.
Allow to cool briefly then puree in blender or food processor.
You may have to do in batches.
Return the puree to saucepan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in the sliced mushrooms.
Add cooked small pasta, if desired.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients.
Brown pie shell in conventional oven in a glass pie dish.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in microwave 15 to 20 minutes on Medium.

title: drunken wieners
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add tomato paste, salt, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add wieners and bourbon.
Simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Serve warm.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Combine beef with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Pat to fit bottom of small coffee can.
Place carrot strips, onion, potato and corn over beef; sprinkle with salt, pepper and olives.
Cover; cook over medium hot coals for 50 minutes.
This recipe will serve 1 person.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: marinated spareribs in crock-pot
directions: Stir together and marinate with ribs overnight.
Set at room temperature and place in crock-pot.
Cook on high 1 to 2 hours, then on low about 5 to 7 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add flour.
Cook until all blended.
Add milk (a little at a time).
Add 4 ounces cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir until blended.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Place noodles in pan, then add the cheese sauce and mix.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: italian strawberry water ice
directions: Combine sugar and water in medium saucepan.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves; boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Force strawberries through food mill or blend in electric blender; strain to remove seeds.
Blend strawberry puree, lemon and orange juices into cool syrup.
Pour into ice cube trays.
Wrap trays in aluminum foil. Freeze until firm.
Twenty minutes before serving, remove from freezer to soften slightly.
Serve in sherbet glasses with champagne.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Blend yogurt and Cool Whip until smooth.
Place in prepared graham cracker crust and place in freezer.
Freeze thoroughly. Remove about 1 hour before serving.

title: london chicken
directions: Pour cans of soup over chicken and arrange slices of mushrooms on top. Pour wine over all. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: anita's chopped eggplant
directions: Select firm, ripe eggplant with no bruises.
Wrap in heavy wax paper and bake as directed.
Remove from oven, peel into chopping bowl.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Chop medium fine.
Grate in onion.
Add crushed garlic, salt and pepper. Stir in vinegar and oil.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with bread rounds, crackers or as a side dish.
For a variation, use diced tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie - our best
directions: Line pan with 2 cups berries.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pie.
Umm, umm.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and add all other ingredients except sour cream. Pour half of mixture in large bowl and let congeal. Spread sour cream over the Jell-O mixture. Pour remaining Jell-O mixture over the sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: poppy seed bread #2
directions: Combine Bisquick, cheese and poppy seed.
Add egg and milk; mix just enough to blend, then beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Turn into a well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with additional poppy seed.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and let it cool in order for it to slice well.

title: layered salad
directions: First Layer:
Your favorite greens to equal about 1 1/2 heads. Place in a large straight sided clear bowl.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Soak beans several hours.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, water to cover and 1/2 the cubed bacon.
Cook until beans are tender; drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Brown onion and garlic in bacon fat. Add next 5 ingredients and bean liquid.
Simmer 15 minutes. Alternate beans and sauce in a casserole.
Cover with remaining bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easiest every spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and beef in oil.
When beef has lost its red color, add 1 can tomato paste.
Stir.
Add 2 cans water; stir.
Add second can of tomato paste; stir.
Add remaining water, salt, pepper, garlic and parsley.
Cook for approximately 3 1/2 to 4 hours, until on the thick side.
Use a heavy steel pot; cover.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto baking sheet to form crust. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add cheese until melted. Remove from heat. In a separate bowl, mix sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Add butter and cheese mix. Mix with frozen hash browns. Spread in large casserole dish. Slightly dot the top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Melt butter. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until set and brown.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Add brown sugar to sauerkraut and kielbasa.
The more brown sugar you add, the darker and sweeter the sauerkraut will be.
Can be cooked on top of stove or baked in oven.

title: skillet gumbo
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice in heavy skillet. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Replace lid and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients on waxed paper.
Sift again into an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Make three little wells in the dry ingredients and pour the salad oil into one, the vinegar into another and the vanilla into the other.
Add milk and stir with a fork until mixture is blended.
Bake in this pan in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large, heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over heat for 2 to 3 minutes to melt sugar crystals on sides of pan.
Uncover.
Add peanuts and cook, stirring occasionally, to hard-crack stage (300°).
Stir in butter and soda.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: polish christmas cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Boil Hartshorn in 2 tablespoons water until dissolved.
Add anise oil, Hartshorn and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Sift baking powder and 2 cups flour into creamed mixture and beat.
Alternate milk and enough flour to stiffen.
Roll out on floured surface to desired thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with a Crisco frosting and dip into colored sugars within the same 24 hours.
Bake thin and crispy or thick and cakey.
Yields 500 to 1000 cookies.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: norwegian bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together with sugar.
Make a well and add other ingredients to dry mixture; mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: savory select spread
directions: Drain tuna and mash with a fork.
Mix together the Ranch dressing, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice and stir thoroughly into the tuna.
Mound a spoonful of tuna onto a toasted cracker and garnish as desired.

title: pie dough(making pies is a good way to get your hands on some dough.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and salt with shortening.
Add iced water and mix well with your hands.
Separate dough into two balls.
Lay ball on floured surface, then turn over.

title: food for gods cake
directions: Cut dates in 3 pieces.
Put soda over dates.
Add boiling water and let cool.
Put eggs, sugar, oleo, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Put in an angel food cake pan.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in large plastic bag and shake until potatoes are coated.
Put in shallow baking pan, discard bag.
Bake 40 minutes, stir occasionally.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: harbor lights pineapple fritters
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop into deep fryer by spoonfuls.
Fry until golden brown, then roll in cinnamon sugar.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot fat; brown onion in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, in moderate oven.

title: molasses squares
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, molasses and vanilla.
Add unbeaten egg, then soda mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet, then sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fluffy muffins
directions: Add your favorites to this basic muffin (berries, nuts, raisins, spices, chocolate chips, etc.).
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Add sugar to eggs, then add butter followed by other ingredients.
Pack in boxes in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix together nuts, sugar and butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
When cool, break and put back in pan (break crust until crumbly).

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk and vanilla.
Place six 5-ounce custard cups in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water around cups one inch deep.
Pour in custard.
Bake in 325° oven 40 to 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
For one large custard, bake in a one-quart casserole 60 minutes or until done.
Do not cut until it is completely cool.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Cook the cornstarch, 2 tablespoons of sugar and water in small saucepan until thickened and mixture is clear.
Let cool.
Beat the egg whites and salt until stiff.
Fold in cornstarch mixture and continue beating until creamy.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Pile meringue on pie.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham and swiss quiche
directions: Bake at
450° for 10 to 15 minutes (until set);
reduce to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Break graham crackers into fourths and line a cookie sheet. Cook
brown sugar and margarine and nuts for 2 minutes after it bubbles but don't boil it.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: popovers
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into well-greased deep muffin cups (3/4 full).
Bake at 425° until golden brown, 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately. Makes 5 to 9 popovers.

title: leconte sunrise juice
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor; place in freezer until almost completely frozen.
Re-blend and serve.

title: brandy slush
directions: Place the tea bags into 2 cups of boiling water until tea is made; remove tea bags.
Stir in 2 cups of sugar until dissolved. Add remaining 7 cups boiling water until well mixed.
Let mixture cool, then add orange juice, lemonade and peach brandy.
Place mixture in freezer containers and put in freezer for several days until it is frozen.
Scrape frozen mixture with a spoon and fill glass two-thirds full.
Add 7-Up and stir until well mixed.

title: "popeye's" biscuits
directions: Mix together and pat out on wax paper coated with Bisquick. Cut out biscuits and place in 9 x 12 pan that contains 1/2 stick melted butter. Pour another 1/2 stick melted butter on top of biscuits. Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: pineapple meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients except the sweet and sour sauce or the barbecue sauce.
Divide into 6 equal portions.
Shape into 4 x 2-inch loaf.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes and top each with 1 teaspoon of the sweet and sour or barbecue sauce.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli according to directions.
Saute celery and onion.
Melt Cheez Whiz in 1/2 cup water.
Combine all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add 1 cup flour, shortening, salt and egg.
Add rest of flour.
Cover and let rise until double.
Stir down and put in greased muffin pans.
Let double.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: no-fry eggplant parmigiana
directions: Add sugar to spaghetti sauce; stir and set aside.
Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In oiled 10 x 6-inch baking dish, place half of eggplant slices.
Spoon on half of sauce.
Top with half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until top is browned and eggplant is tender. Let stand 10 minutes for easier serving.

title: nutcracker punch
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, mix sugar and water.
Heat until mixture is clear, then let cool completely.
Dissolve Fruit Fresh in water, lemon juice, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Add mixture to cooled syrup.
This will keep in the fridge for several weeks.

title: wild rice stuffing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in bread crumbs and heat until light brown.
Mix 1/2 the crumbs with seasonings.
Add enough liquid to moisten.
Makes 4 1/2 cups of stuffing.

title: hulda fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, salt and milk in a thick pan.
Cook 6 minutes after it starts boiling.
Take off stove and add marshmallow cream, nuts and silver bells.
Stir well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: dillman farm persimmon pudding
directions: Combine pulp, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour with baking powder.

Add to pulp mixture alternately with a combination of the cream, buttermilk and soda. Use a pastry brush to coat baking pan well with melted butter. Stir remaining butter into pulp mixture. Stir in cinnamon.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for half an hour.

title: beef and cheese pasta
directions: Cook ground beef in a little oil; drain off fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes, or until onions are soft.
Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.
Put macaroni in dish, then sauce.
Spread with sour cream.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (covered).
Makes large baking dish.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter. Boil for 3 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts. Beat until creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: sesame dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together in a covered jar.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetarian dressing
directions: Make boxed chicken dressing using juice from soymeat and the potato water.
Saute soymeat.
Add soymeat to dressing.
Add onion and cornbread.
Add eggs, hard-boiled and scrambled.
Add margarine.
Secret to dressing is to keep it moist.
Add more flavored water as necessary.
Bake in low oven as any other dressing.
Great with holiday dinners.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook rosamarina 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook juices form oranges and pineapple with flour, eggs, salt and sugar.
Cook until slightly thick (will be runny).
Cool, then add to rosamarina.
Let set overnight.
Next day, add Cool Whip and drained fruit.

title: autumn pumpkin pie
directions: Make pastry for one 9-inch pie.
Beat ingredients together with rotary beater.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish (well-greased).

Mix remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto fruit. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer or until fruit is tender and dough is golden brown. Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: nina's apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in big pot and cook on top of stove until very thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, honey, egg and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Cover. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet, 15 x 10-inch.
Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large mixer bowl on medium for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in Bisquick, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes; cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 50 (3 x 1-inch) bars.
Refrigerate remaining bars.

title: oatmeal lemon-cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine shortening, cream cheese and 1 1/4 cups sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in egg yolk, lemon extract and lemon peel.
Combine flour, oats and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture with spoon until blended.
Drop rounded teaspoons of dough 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Beat whole egg with reserved egg white. Brush over tops of cookies.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Press almond slices lightly on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cook 2 minutes on cookie sheet before removing.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hobo cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add can cream of mushroom soup.
Saute green peppers and onions in butter until soft.
Add to rice mixture.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz, mushrooms and thawed broccoli; mix well.
Put in casserole and top with potato chips or onion rings.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and drain.
Slice thin, as for table use.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over slices.
Mix together lightly. Place in glass jars and refrigerate.
Can be eaten after 24 hours.
Nice and crispy.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in glass baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, water, oil, eggs and pudding.
Mix together the nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Put 1/4 of nut mixture in pan first.
Alternately layer cake mix and nut mixture, finishing with cake mixture on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: hand freezer ice cream
directions: Beat yolks and whites of eggs separately. Add sugar and evaporated milk to yolks; beat well. Fold in beaten egg whites to which salt has been added. Pour into freezer can. Add enough milk to cover top of dasher. Do not overfill. Allow room for expansion in freezing. Freeze according to freezer directions. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In heavy bottomed 4-quart pot, make a dark roux of flour and oil, stirring constantly, so as not to burn.
When brown, add celery, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Stir this roux until vegetables become slightly browned.
Add juice from tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces and add water.
Bring mix to boil, stirring frequently.
Lower to simmer for 30 minutes. Taste for seasoning and add okra; simmer for 1 hour.
Add shrimp and scallops and cook 30 minutes longer, tasting for seasonings. Serve over rice.

title: johnny appleseed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl and whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate. This is a great coleslaw dressing.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: reuben dip
directions: Dice sliced corned beef.
Put all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat 5 minutes over low heat.
Add more milk for spreading consistency.
Serve warm on cocktail rye bread or rye crackers.
May be doubled.

title: boboli(makes four 12-inch pizza-size bobolis)
directions: Mix yeast and sugar with 1/3 cup warm water.
Let foam 5 minutes.
Add salt, 3 cups water and olive oil.
Mix in flour, starting with 5 cups, and adding enough so dough is easy to handle.
Knead 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Get all water out of spinach; add other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: delicious coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring and 1 package coconut; bake according to cake mix directions.
In a 2-cup measuring bowl, mix 2/3 cup evaporated milk, 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring, 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Fill measuring bowl the rest of the way with water and mix.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Cool and top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: *Add cubes to water for cooking rice.

title: goulash
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until well done.
Cook spaghetti in salted water until desired tenderness is reached.
Drain.
Combine hamburger mixture with spaghetti and add tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Rattle Watch:
Volunteer fire groups in the early North American settlements would keep watch in the towns at night and warned the local people of fire by sounding their rattles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli very well. Combine remaining ingredients except butter and crumbs. Add broccoli into mixture. Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add crumbs.
Mix well. Sprinkle crumb mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: angel creme delight
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces; place in a large rectangular pan or glass dish (about 9 x 15-inch).
Mix the sour cream, instant pudding and milk until smooth, by hand; pour over cake pieces.
Garnish with sliced fruits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes for each.
Mix walnuts through 1/2 cup flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
Add remaining flour and milk alternately. Add walnuts.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sunday night kitchen skillet
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat; cook until almost done.
Add 1 cup water; more if necessary.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer cider, sticks and juice for 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients in bag and simmer to taste.

title: grandma's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until spreading consistency. May need to add more milk, a little at a time.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: In skillet, slowly saute chicken in Butter Buds 4 to 5 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Mix cornstarch and juice.
Stir in 57 sauce and marmalade.
Pour into skillet, stirring until thickened.
Place chicken in sauce.
Heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Top with cheese slices. Combine soup, sherry and cream; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing crumbs.
Pour butter over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Miracle Whip, vinegar and garlic salt.
Beat with hand beater until blended.
Chill until partially set.
Add corned beef with any or all of the nuts and vegetables.
Chill until firm.

title: key lime pie
directions: Prepare pudding and chill 30 minutes.
Mash cookies.
Spread bottom and side of pan.
Grate candy bar on top.
Sprinkle some cookie crumbs on top with candy bar.
Put 2 tablespoons Cool Whip in middle and top with 1/2 slice of lime on Cool Whip.

title: hot beef spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: chicken and potato soup with dumplings
directions: In a large pot, season water with salt and pepper.
Add washed, cut up chicken parts.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken and pour broth through strainer; set aside chicken to cool. Saving all the broth, return to stove.
Add onions, celery, carrots and potatoes; adjust seasoning to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and orange juice in bowl.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Stir in flour and soda. Place in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease
pie
plate.
Sprinkle pecans in plate.
Beat remaining
ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: new orleans school of cooking pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240° on candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture thickens, becomes creamy and cloudy and pecans stay suspended in mixture.
Spoon onto buttered waxed paper layered over newspaper.
Will make up to 50, depending in size. Let cool and transfer to covered tins.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Store in air tight container.To make 1 cup of cocoa place 1/3 c. of mixture in a cup of hot water.

title: creamy sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into greased casserole.
Combine flour, salt and brown sugar.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter, marshmallows and almonds.
Cover with cream.
Bake in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large cooking pot.
Simmer well. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake slowly at 325° for 75 to 90 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: sauteed and simmered chicken breasts
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in seasoned flour saving the extra flour.
Brown chicken in large skillet.
Set aside.
In same skillet, saute garlic.
Add chicken stock.
Make thickener from remaining seasoned flour and use to make gravy.
Add soy sauce and brown sugar.
Put chicken breasts back into gravy.
Cover and simmer slowly until chicken is done.
If skillet is too small, transfer everything to larger pot.
Serve with rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, 8 to 15 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: hobo beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot for a couple of hours on low heat.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put first 3
ingredients in enough water to cook broccoli until very tender.
Then add milk.
Melt butter and add flour to butter until thick
like paste.
Add the butter-flour mixture to broccoli-milk mixture and heat until desired thickness.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix 7-Up with marshmallows and heat until melted.
Add Jell-O; stir and dissolve.
Slowly add hot mixture to cream cheese; whip until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until partially set. Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill overnight.
Garnish with sugar frosted grapes, if desired, and serve.
Grapes go into center if you use a ring mold, otherwise around edge of plate.

title: holiday salad
directions: Make jello according to directions, leaving off 1/2 cup liquid. Cool but do not set.
Blend in remaining ingredients.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly pork, ham, onions and Rice Krispies.
Add; stir and combine salt, pepper and tomato juice.
Clean peppers; boil peppers 5 minutes in salt water. Drain.
Fill peppers with meat mixture in greased muffin-pan cups. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Use a
well greased deep pan or Dutch oven.
Pour 2 cans of cherries;
then
pour
over top of fruit the box of dry cake mix and
sprinkle
cinnamon.
Melt butter and pour evenly over dry mix and cinnamon.
Sprinkle nuts and bake in a 350° or 375° oven for 45
minutes to 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Press into 9 x 12 pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until set.
Don't overbake.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Prepare jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the strawberries when the jello is slightly jelled.
Pour over the top of cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix juice, marshmallows, flour, egg, vinegar and sugar.
Cook over medium until thick. Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, add Cool Whip, pineapple, apples and peanuts to sauce.
Mix well and chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt well; sift if necessary. Add milk (use some canned milk).
Stir well and cook until thick; stir constantly.
Beat 3 (or 4 if small) egg yolks in small bowl. Add some of the hot liquid, then stir this into the pie filling and cook about 2 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, salt, sugar and water; let stand 45 minutes. Beat egg.
Add oil and sugar and add to yeast mixture with 1 cup warm water.
Add flour.
Let rise double in bulk; knead about 3 minutes.
Let rise double in bulk again.
Form rolls and let rise. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; sprinkle over chicken. Brown slowly in butter; remove from pan. In same pan, cook onion until tender. Move onions aside and place chicken in pan.
Add mushrooms and tarragon; spoon with onions over chicken.
Add water; cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: honey-cashew ranch dressing
directions: Put mayonnaise in a mixing bowl and slowly add salad oil; mix until totally combined, then add honey, white vinegar, lemon juice and teriyaki sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Finally, add the dill and cashews.
Season to taste.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole peanuts, syrup, salt and sugar.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Take out; stir. Microwave 4 more minutes.
Take out.
Add vanilla and margarine. Microwave 2 more minutes.
Take out; stir in baking soda (quickly).
Mixture will foam.
Pour out onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Sift flour; measure; add baking powder and salt, sift again. Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or 2 knives, blending it until the mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Stirring with fork, add enough milk to make soft dough, or until flour leaves sides of bowl and follows fork; continue until all flour disappears.
Turn out on floured board; knead for about 1/2 minute.
Pat out to 1 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter; place close together on lightly greased baking sheet. Brush tops lightly with melted butter or margarine.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cover for 30 minutes before serving.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Beat egg; add buttermilk and mix.
Add corn meal, baking powder, salt and soda.
Put about 2 tablespoons oil in iron skillet and heat to 425°.
Add mix and cook until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add oil.
Thicken with flour.
Add liquid and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate the cheese in food processor.
Grate the frozen butter in the food processor. Take out the grating blade and put in knife blade.
Add 2 cups of flour to the butter.
Beat a few minutes. Add 1/3 of the cheese and beat again.
Add 1/3 more cheese and beat again, then add remainder of cheese, paprika and salt.
Beat all together until it gets to the ball stage.
Take out of machine and let sit on the counter for about 1/2 hour to soften. Add Rice Krispies and toss. Form into small balls.
Put them on a cookie sheet.
Freeze for about 15 minutes. Remove from freezer and put into individual freezer bags.
Preheat oven to 375° and reheat frozen balls for about 15 minutes.

title: oriental appetizers
directions: Cut crescent rolls into thirds.
Brown ground beef and onions. Drain.
Drain bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Mix everything together.
Spread thin layer of mustard on crescent pieces.
Put small spoonfuls of mixture in center of crescent pieces.
Bring sides of roll up and pinch closed.
Put on baking sheets and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fruit parfaits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Combine orange, banana and pineapple.
Toss lightly.
Spoon alternate layers of fruit mixture and orange juice mixture into 6 parfait glasses. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Then serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and boil first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly, until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and beat until quite thick.
Pour onto buttered plate and let cool.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half of milk into batter. Add soda to remaining half and stir into the batter.
Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Two cups of chocolate chips may be added to this recipe, if desired.

title: turkey sausage(for a very low-fat breakfast treat)
directions: Mix together.
Form into patties or links; fry as regular sausage.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Add sugar, salt and spices to vinegar.
Dilute 1/2 with water if strong.
Simmer about 8 minutes.
Strain and pour over the peeled eggs arranged in quart jar.
Seal and let stand 2 days before using.
Add sprig of dill, a few caraway seed, a slice of garlic, a clove or onions to brine as desired.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and eggs together. Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon together. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix cherries, pineapple and pecans with 1 cup flour.
Combine with batter. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 3-quart baking dish lightly. Scald 2 cups milk in 3-quart saucepan over low heat. Add cornmeal gradually; stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in 1 cup milk, salt, pepper, baking powder and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks and fold into mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pat's poppy cock
directions: Spread popped corn on large cookie sheet and add pecans and/or peanuts.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, Karo syrup and salt and bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda, butter flavoring and vanilla.
Stir.
Dribble over popcorn and stir well.
Place in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate and let congeal.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake yellow cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool for 30 minutes.
Cover with pineapple.
Let juice saturate cake.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Let stand 4 or 5 minutes, then mix with cream cheese.
Spread on top of pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip; top with coconut or nuts.

title: baked lasagne(from 1975 edition)
directions: Saute meat in oil into small pieces until brown.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes or longer.
Cook lasagne as directed on package.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Gradually add flour, alternating with milk; mix well.
Blend in flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check for doneness.
If needed, bake another 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Take juice from pineapple and blueberries and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil and add raspberry Jell-O and 1 cup cold water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Let congeal.

title: cherry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water or part water and part pineapple juice. Stir in cherry pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: lemonade spritzer
directions: Pour over ice cubes in 12 ounce glass.
Fill with ginger ale. Serve.

title: stuffed green peppers with tomato sauce
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds and set tops aside.
Remove stem.
Brown beef and remove from heat.
Add onions, celery, rice, milk, egg, salt, pepper and chili powder to ground beef and mix. Stuff peppers with mixture.
In pot, combine tomato soup and water. Place pepper tops in bottom of pot.
Set stuffed peppers on top to prevent from spilling.
Place pot on stove at medium-high for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until hamburger is done, or simmer for 2 hours.
Keep warm until served.

title: dreamy high pumpkin pie
directions: In separate bowl mix gelatin and water; set aside.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until thick and lemony-looking.
Mix pumpkin with milk, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add egg yolk mixture.
Cook over hot water until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add gelatin mixture, stir and cool.
Beat egg whites alternately adding 1/2 cup sugar until very stiff.
With 1/2 cup heavy cream, whipped, or Cool Whip, fold egg whites into cooled custard.
Spoon into baked pie shell and chill overnight.
When ready to serve, whip remaining cup of heavy cream (or use Cool Whip) and spread on top.
Sprinkle moist toasted coconut on top of pie.

title: no fat cornbread
directions: Put meal in medium sized bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir with spoon until well mixed.
Mold into 3-inch patties.
Fry in hot oil or bacon grease until brown.

title: london broil
directions: Place steak in a gallon size sealable bag.
Add wine, garlic, pepper and rosemary.
Lightly massage marinade into meat.
Seal bag, squeezing out air; turn to coat steak.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Remove meat from refrigerator at least 30 minutes before broiling or grilling. Lift meat from marinade and discard marinade.
You can either broil or grill.

title: dessert brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt and nuts.
Add butter and cocoa. Place in a greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. When done scatter top with miniature marshmallows and return to oven to melt.
When soft, spread evenly with fork over top.
When cool, ice.
Mix cocoa, margarine, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Spread on brownies.

title: plum cake
directions: Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Boil macaroni and drain. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, egg and cheese well.
Fold in broccoli.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 package of Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
(One cup of cooked, diced chicken can be added.)

title: honey roasted party mix
directions: Mix cereals, snacks and pretzels in large roaster. Heat brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup, sugar and honey in saucepan or in microwave on High until comes to boil. Stir in the baking soda and pour over the cereal mixture, stirring until evenly coated. Heat oven to 325° and bake 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes. Spread on waxed paper and cool completely. Store in airtight container.

title: bean and meat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Brown onions and ground beef in large skillet; drain. Add beans and barbecue sauce. Pour into baking dish. Top with slice cheese. Tear biscuits in half and place on top of cheese. Bake 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 375° for 1 hour.

title: wine-baked chicken(low-fat)
directions: Place chicken breasts, bone side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange mushrooms around chicken.
Pour wine over chicken and sprinkle with parsley, tarragon, salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Serve with rice and fresh asparagus.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil the lasagna until tender.
Cook hamburger meat.
Drain. Mix in spaghetti sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer lasagna, meat mixture, then cheeses.
Do another layer.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: okra-corn-tomato vinaigrette
directions: Wash okra; blanch in 2 cups boiling water 1 minute or until crisp-tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water; cool.
Remove and discard ends.
Cut okra into 1/2 inch slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix in cooked mushroom and celery soup.
Add sauteed onion.
Melt Cheez Whiz and pour on top.
Add croutons or bread crumbs and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and margarine.
Mix together eggs, mushroom and celery soup, mayonnaise and cheese and 2 teaspoons lemon juice. Add sauteed onions; mix well.
Line bottom of casserole dish with broccoli; layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Pour mixture on top. Spread remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: german apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Combine the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Add to egg mixture and mix well. Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9 baking dish at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: shrimp and crab gumbo
directions: (1.) Mix bell peppers, onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves in a gallon of boiling water. Reduce heat and continue cooking until Step #5 is complete.

title: orange-poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Makes 1 cup; 30 calories per 2 tablespoons.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Mix butter, soy sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Brush on salmon steaks.
Grill 10 minutes on one side. Baste and turn fish.
Grill for 8 to 10 minutes more.
Cooking time will depend on thickness of the fish.
Baste the fish frequently during grilling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together creamed corn and cream cheese.
Add oil and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Grease loaf pan or iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mash ground chuck down in a pan and add enough water to cover. Heat to a boil and mash right away with potato masher to break up.
Add paprika, chili powder, cumin and salt to taste.
Add catsup, if desired.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add other ingredients.
Cook in slow cooker on high for 8 hours.

title: arabic coffee(kahwa)
directions: In a brass coffee pot or regular saucepan, bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add coffee and cardamom, stirring constantly. When mixture comes to a boil and becomes frothy, remove from fire and stir until froth has subsided.
Repeat this process two more times.
After the coffee has foamed and subsided for the third time, pour into Arabic coffee cups.
Serve kahwa very hot (a minute or two after pouring in cups to allow the grounds to settle in the bottom).
Serves 6.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
In a greased pan, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 of noodles and 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles, then remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with rest of Mozzarella.
Pour water around the edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn hash
directions: Mix together and chill several hours before serving cold. Great, quick salad or vegetable with grilled meats and potatoes.

title: red-white-blue jello delight
directions: Make raspberry gelatin according to package directions.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch glass pan and chill until firm.

title: low calorie jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; set aside until room temperature.
Add to Jell-O the pineapple with juice, strawberries with juice, then fold in bananas.
Pour half in dish; chill until set.
When set, spread sour cream over top.
Finish by pouring rest of Jell-O mixture over top.
Refrigerate until serving. Enjoy!

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until well mixed. Bake in lightly greased muffin tins at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad no. 2
directions: Add together all ingredients and congeal.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Over medium heat in hot margarine cook onions until lightly browned.
Add meat, paprika and salt.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is fork-tender.
Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil).
Serve over hot noodles.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in ungreased pan.
Make 3 holes.
In hole #1 put melted butter, in hole #2 put vinegar and in hole #3 put vanilla.
Over all that, put cold water.
Mix.
Bake in oven at 375° until done.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Combine eggs and shortening.
Add half the dry cake mix; beat well.
Add remaining dry mix, nuts and coconut; mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with Melba toast rounds or Ritz crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken salad bake
directions: Spray a 1 1/2 quart casserole with vegetable oil and preheat oven to 400°.
Combine chicken, celery, onion, water chestnuts, cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle with either shoestring potatoes, chips, or noodles.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas and nuts.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
When done (a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean), turn cake out of pan and cool.
Dust cake lightly with sifted confectioners sugar and serve.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: For easier handling and clean up, line cookie sheet with foil, forming edges all around.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in deep dish; grate cheese over top.
Cover with Ritz crackers, crushed.
Roll in with crackers 1 stick margarine.
Spread on casserole.
Put in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Make into patties, brown on both sides.
Then place 1 slice onion on top each patty.
Make gravy by directions on package and pour over patties and onion. Cover and cook on low 35 minutes.

title: mashed potato klushki
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into snake shape on a floured board. Cut into bite size pillow shape pieces.
Drop into boiling salted water, when they float to top, boil 2 minutes.
Drain.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos a few at a time in a blender.
Mix with melted margarine.
Reserve 1 cup and press remaining in 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice ice cream and lay on top of cookies.
Spread hot fudge on top of ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip on fudge.
Sprinkle with rest of cookies.
Freeze until serving time.

title: walnut drop cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in 1 cup nuts.
Drop teaspoonful dough on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with minced nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ice cream jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate until firm. Can be poured into any type of jello mold.

title: orange whip salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with drained pineapple and mandarin oranges. Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Add pecans.
Mix well. Refrigerate and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce for 100 people
directions: Saute 1/2 cup olive oil and 1 cup chopped onion in pan.
Place in bottom of Nesco.
Brown ground pork and beef, if used.
Put in Nesco.
If using meatballs, put meatballs in Nesco.
Add rest of the ingredients except spaghetti noodles.
Simmer for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add water, undrained tomatoes and beans, tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Pass cheese, chips and sour cream as toppings.
Serves 6.

title: soy sauce
directions: Peel and slice
tomatoes.
Slice
onions
over this and add salt.
Let stand
overnight.
The next morning, rinse with clear water.
Add spices
and vinegar.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add sugar. Cook 30 minutes more.
Put in jars and cold pack 10 to 15 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice.
Stir in Jell-O.
Stir in Cool Whip until all lumps are gone.
Add milk and nuts.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and cover with water. Add salt. Boil for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove from broth and save broth. When cool enough to handle, pick meat from bones. Make gravy with broth, using flour and water thickening. Boil noodles until tender. Drain and place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add chicken and enough gravy to cover noodles. Melt butter and add to bread crumbs; add cheese and spread mixture over chicken noodle mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, until nicely browned.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Read all directions before beginning.

title: simple punch
directions: Let sherbet soften. Pour ginger-ale and Hawaiian Punch over sherbet. Mix and serve out of large punch bowl.

title: piney wood hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; beat milk and egg together and combine with dry ingredients; batter should hold its shape when picked up with a spoon. If dough is too soft, add more cornmeal. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook about 1 1/2 minutes on one side; turn and cook on other side for 1 minute. Makes about 45 hush puppies.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix together sugar, soda and buttermilk in a large pan.
On low heat sit until mixture boils.
Boil to "soft ball" stage.
Remove from heat; add nuts, vanilla and a lump of butter.
Beat mixture with a spoon until thick.
Slightly cool and drop by tablespoon onto buttered wax paper.
You have to be quick when you start to spoon it out or the whole batch will set up on you in the bowl.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beating vigorously until well mixed.
Pour batter into hot pan sprayed with original Pam.
(Heat Pam sprayed pan in 450° oven for 3 minutes.) Use square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake in hot oven at 450°, preheated, for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to instructions.
Drain and place in large mixing bowl.
Cook broccoli just until tender.
Cook carrots just until tender.
Drain both and combine with tortellini.
Add peppers and fresh basil and toss.
Whip yolk, lemon juice, mustard and vinegar.
Pour oils in a thin steady stream to make a light mayonnaise.
Pour dressing over salad and toss to coat.
Serve at room temperature or slightly chilled.
Serves 8 to 10.
Looks festive and can be served meatless.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add eggs, lightly beaten. Stir.
In skillet, low temperature, fry in oil (about 1 1/2 to 2 Tbsp. per patty).
Pour 1/4 cup egg mixture at a time into skillet. Push cooked egg up with broad spatula to form a patty. Cook until patty is set; turn.
Serve with heated sauce, mixture of soup and soy sauce.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until boiling.
Boil about 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Pour over corn flakes; mix good.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix together rice, soup mix, soup and water.
Let stand 5 minutes, then pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add bouillon cube.

title: wonderful fruit dip
directions: Mix with beater.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or so.
Serve with fresh fruit, melon, cantaloupes, grapes and strawberries.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain all fruit completely.
Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients and mix well with mixture.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until onions are soft. Blend in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add milk and soy sauce; cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in chicken.
Add drained water chestnuts; stir.

title: orange slice (candy) cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add brown sugar, white sugar and eggs. Cream together. Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt together; add to the creamed mixture. Add oats and coconut; mix with first ingredients. Mix in the orange slice pieces.
Drop by spoonfuls on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly and boil until mixture spins a long thread (234°).
Take out 1 cup and gradually pour over beaten egg whites.
When rest of syrup cracks when dropped in cold water-test (270°), take from heat and pour slowly over first part, mixing constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts if desired.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Reserving 1/2 cup coconut, toast remaining coconut.
Bake pie shell 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cut half the meat from bone and brown.
Add remaining meat and bone to cold water.
Add browned meat, onion and salt to cold water with meat.
Cook slowly for a couple hours.
Add vegetables; continue cooking until done.
This soup is better if used next day.

title: hamburger-biscuit casserole
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Add onion and mushrooms. Cook until onion and mushrooms are soft.
Add 1/2 cup of sour cream and mushroom soup to mixture.
Place in 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Gently stir in 1 can of dried onions.
Bake at 350° until it begins to bubble (approximately 25 to 30 minutes). Then place biscuits on two sides of dish.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup of sour cream with egg.
Brush over biscuits.
Place other can of onions in middle of biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf topping
directions: Mix well and pour over any meat loaf and bake.

title: steak sauce
directions: In a skillet, brown chopped onion in a little butter.
Add beef bouillon.
Simmer.
Add garlic seasoning, salt, pepper and drained mushrooms.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Add flour (the old-fashioned way:
add some hot liquid from skillet to the flour in a cup; when flour and liquid are a thin and smooth consistency, add to skillet mixture).
Add red wine.
Makes 2 to 3 cups of sauce, enough for 8 steaks.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Soak bulghur in water to cover for 1 hour.
Squeeze dry by pressing between palms.
In a large salad bowl, combine bulghur, green onions, parsley, mint and tomatoes; mix well.
Stir in lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper; mix well.
Serve with large lettuce leaves to use as scoops.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix ingredients, except cabbage, and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
When cool, pour over grated cabbage and mix well.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Beat in sugar, salt, cornstarch and butter gradually.
Pour in milk and blend.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add coconut and cool.
Add flavoring and nutmeg and pour into shell.
Cover with meringue and bake 15 to 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Remove meat.
If desired, thicken sauce to serve with meat.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Add sugar, then add flour alternating with an egg, until all flour and eggs have been added.
Add lemon extract and gradually fold in 7-Up.
Pour in lightly greased tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not open oven while baking.
Cool in pan for 3 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake cornbread and crumble into mixing bowl. Saute onion in margarine. Add onion and remaining ingredients to crumbled cornbread. Mix well; pour into buttered or oiled casserole dish. Bake at 350° until set and browned around edges. Top with cheese after taking out of oven, if desired.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine meat and milk; divide into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, pat each patty to approximately a 6-inch circle.
May need a little flour to aid in this process.
Place a portion of stuffing in center of each patty and proceed to draw meat over the stuffing, creating a bundle. Place bundles in casserole dish.
Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce and 1 soup can water.
Pour over bundles and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian shoyu chicken
directions: Heat shoyu and water.
When hot, add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add garlic, ginger and chicken; cook over medium heat until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally so chicken browns evenly.

title: polish sausage-kraut skillet
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook
onion
and garlic in butter or margarine until onion is tender,
but
not
brown.
Stir in potatoes, carrots, water, bouillon granules, sugar and caraway seed.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover
and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables
are
tender.
Place sauerkraut and Polish sausages atop vegetables.
Cover;
cook
15 minutes more or until sausages are
heated
through.
Stir
flour into sour cream;
stir into the
sausage-kraut
mixture
and
heat through. Season to taste with
salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley. Makes 5 servings.
